{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719867431,"sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"tool_0dnNoA0GS4e9KgigiMDLseWj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/002-memory-store-and-search/019-maintenance-grace-daemon-survives-reelection/resource-map.md 2>/dev/null || echo \"NO_RESOURCE_MAP\"","description":"Check for resource-map.md existence"},"output":"NO_RESOURCE_MAP\n","metadata":{"output":"NO_RESOURCE_MAP\n","exit":0,"description":"Check for resource-map.md existence","truncated":false},"title":"Check for resource-map.md existence","time":{"start":1781719867424,"end":1781719867426}},"id":"prt_ed6c79794001pQai2EbPle2Mnt","sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","messageID":"msg_ed6c75a86001qw2iF87z3LK0Ab"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719868300,"sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_OHzDNvbMR8gVM7auEghKWBWi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n7:   - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n8:   - \"review stuck detection\"\n9:   - \"composite convergence vote\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Convergence\n15: \n16: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n25: \n26: | Outcome | Meaning |\n27: |---------|---------|\n28: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n29: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n30: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n31: \n32: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n33: \n34: Release-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n35: - `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n36: - `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n37: - `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n38: \n39: When the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n40: \n41: ### When to Use\n42: \n43: - Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n44: - Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n45: - Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n46: - Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n47: \n48: ### Key Defaults\n49: \n50: | Setting | Value | Purpose |\n51: |---------|-------|---------|\n52: | `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n53: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n54: | `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n55: | `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n56: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n57: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n58: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n59: \n60: ### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n61: \n62: `convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n63: \n64: **Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n65: \n66: | Skill | Default | Signal |\n67: |---|---|---|\n68: | `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n69: | `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n70: | `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n71: \n72: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n73: \n74: ### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n75: \n76: > **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n77: \n78: For review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n79: \n80: | Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n81: |---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n82: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n83: | `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n84: | `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n85: \n86: When implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n87: \n88: ### Shared Stop Contract\n89: \n90: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n91: \n92: #### stopReason Enum\n93: \n94: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n95: |--------------|---------|\n96: | `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n97: | `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n98: | `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n99: | `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n100: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n101: | `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n102: | `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n103: \n104: #### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n105: \n106: `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n107: \n108: ```json\n109: {\n110:   \"type\": \"event\",\n111:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n112:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n113:   \"run\": 5,\n114:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n115:   \"gateResults\": {\n116:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n117:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n118:       \"pass\": false,\n119:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n120:       \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n121:     },\n122:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n123:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n124:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n125:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n126:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n127:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n128:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n129:   },\n130:   \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n131:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n132:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n133:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n134:   \"generation\": 1\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: - `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n139: - `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n140: - `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n141: - `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n142: - When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n143: \n144: ### Decision Priority\n145: \n146: Checks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n147: \n148: 1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n149: 2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n150: 3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n151: 4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n152: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n153: 6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 2. HARD STOPS\n158: \n159: Hard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n160: \n161: ### Max Iterations Reached\n162: \n163: ```\n164: if len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n165:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: The loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n169: \n170: ### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n171: \n172: ```\n173: if coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n174:   if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n175:     if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n176:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n184: \n185: Identifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n186: \n187: ```\n188: function countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n189:   count = 0\n190:   for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n191:     if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n192:     if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n193:     if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n194:       count += 1\n195:     else:\n196:       break\n197:   return count\n198: ```\n199: \n200: **Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n201: \n202: **Status exclusions:**\n203: - `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n204: - `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n205: \n206: When `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n207: \n208: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n213: \n214: Three independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n215: \n216: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n217: |--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n218: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n219: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n220: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n221: \n222: ### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n223: \n224: Averages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n225: \n226: ```\n227: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n228:   recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n229:   avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n230:   rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n234: \n235: Robust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n236: \n237: ```\n238: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n239:   allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n240:   med = median(allRatios)\n241:   mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n242:   noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n243:   madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n247: \n248: Highest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n249: \n250: ```\n251: dimensionStop =\n252:   dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n253:   AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n254:   AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n255: ```\n256: \n257: The latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n258: \n259: ### Weighted Vote\n260: \n261: ```\n262: stopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\n263: if stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n264: ```\n265: \n266: Weights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n267: \n268: ### Semantic Convergence Signals\n269: \n270: Two additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n271: \n272: #### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n273: \n274: Measures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n275: \n276: | Value | Meaning |\n277: |-------|---------|\n278: | 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n279: | 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n280: | 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n281: | 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n282: \n283: Computation:\n284: ```\n285: function computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n286:   newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n287:   totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n288:   if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n289:   return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n290: ```\n291: \n292: When `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n293: \n294: #### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n295: \n296: Measures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n297: \n298: | Value | Meaning |\n299: |-------|---------|\n300: | 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n301: | 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n302: | 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n303: | 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n304: \n305: Computation:\n306: ```\n307: function computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n308:   if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n309:   unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n310:     if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n311:     and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n312:   totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n313:   if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n314:   return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n315: ```\n316: \n317: Convergence behavior:\n318: - `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n319: - `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n320: \n321: #### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n322: \n323: The two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n324: \n325: 1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n326:    - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n327:    - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n328: \n329: 2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n330: \n331: The gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n332: \n333: #### Stop-Decision Trace\n334: \n335: The stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n336: \n337: ```json\n338: {\n339:   \"type\": \"event\",\n340:   \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n341:   \"semanticSignals\": {\n342:     \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n343:     \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n344:   },\n345:   \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n346:   ...\n347: }\n348: ```\n349: \n350: | `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n351: |-------------------|---------|\n352: | `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n353: | `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n354: | `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n355: | `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n356: \n357: ### Graceful Degradation\n358: \n359: | Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n360: |---------------------|----------------|----------|\n361: | 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n362: | 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n363: | 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n364: \n365: Semantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n370: \n371: The review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n372: \n373: ### Severity Weights\n374: \n375: | Severity | Weight | Description |\n376: |----------|--------|-------------|\n377: | **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n378: | **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n379: | **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n380: \n381: ### Computation\n382: \n383: ```\n384: SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\n385: refinementMultiplier = 0.5\n386: \n387: weightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\n388: weightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\n389: weightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n390: \n391: newFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n392: ```\n393: \n394: - `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n395: - `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n396: - `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n397: \n398: ### P0 Override Rule\n399: \n400: ```\n401: if ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n402:   newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n403: \n404: if total_findings == 0:\n405:   newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n406: ```\n407: \n408: A new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n409: \n410: ---\n411: \n412: ## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n413: \n414: > **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n415: \n416: Deep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n417: \n418: | Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n419: |------|------|------|-------------|\n420: | **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n421: | **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n422: | **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n423: | **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n424: | **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n425: | (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n426: | **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n427: | **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n428: | **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n429: \n430: ### Gate Evaluation\n431: \n432: ```\n433: function buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n434:   gateResults = {\n435:     findingStability: {\n436:       pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n437:       detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n438:     },\n439:     dimensionCoverage: {\n440:       pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n441:             coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n442:             coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n443:       detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n444:     },\n445:     p0Resolution: {\n446:       pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n447:       detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n448:     },\n449:     evidenceDensity: {\n450:       pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n451:       detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n452:     },\n453:     hotspotSaturation: {\n454:       pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n455:       detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n456:     },\n457:     fixCompletenessReplay: {\n458:       pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n459:       detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n460:     },\n461:     candidateCoverage: {\n462:       pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n463:       detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n464:     },\n465:     graphlessFallback: {\n466:       pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n467:       detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n468:     }\n469:   }\n470: \n471:   blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n472:   return {\n473:     pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n474:     blockedBy,\n475:     gateResults\n476:   }\n477: ```\n478: \n479: When convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n480: \n481: ### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n482: \n483: | Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n484: |-------------|-------------------|\n485: | `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n486: | `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n487: | `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n488: | `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n489: | `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n490: | `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n491: | `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n492: | `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n493: \n494: ### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n495: \n496: Use this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n497: \n498: | Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n499: |--------------|------------------|--------------|\n500: | `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n501: | `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n502: | `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n503: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n504: | `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n505: | `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n506: | `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n507: | `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n508: | `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n509: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n510: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n511: | `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n516: \n517: The provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n518: \n519: | Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n520: |---------|-----------|---------|\n521: | **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n522: | **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n523: | **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n524: \n525: ### Determination\n526: \n527: ```\n528: function determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n529:   activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n530:   activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n531:   activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n532: \n533:   if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n534:     return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n535:   if activeP1 > 0:\n536:     return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n537: \n538:   hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n539:   return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ### Post-Verdict Routing\n543: \n544: | Verdict | Next Step |\n545: |---------|-----------|\n546: | FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n547: | CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n548: | PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n549: \n550: ---\n551: \n552: ## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n553: \n554: Stuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n559: \n560: The following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n561: \n562: ### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n563: \n564: | Field | Default | Range | Description |\n565: |-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n566: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n567: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n568: | `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n569: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n570: \n571: ### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n572: \n573: The following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n574: \n575: - `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n576: - `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n577: - Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n578: - Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n579: - Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n580: \n581: ### Canonical Manifest\n582: \n583: The authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n584: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`\n\n(End of file - total 584 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nConvergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n| **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n| **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n\nConvergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n\nRelease-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n- `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n- `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n- `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n\nWhen the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n- Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n- Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n- Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n\n### Key Defaults\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n| `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n\n`convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n\n**Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n\n| Skill | Default | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n| `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n| `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n\n### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n\n> **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n\nFor review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n\n| Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n| `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n| `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n\nWhen implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n\n### Shared Stop Contract\n\nEvery terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n#### stopReason Enum\n\n| `stopReason` | Meaning |\n|--------------|---------|\n| `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n| `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n| `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n| `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n| `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n\n#### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n\n`step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n- `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n- `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n- `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n- When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n\n### Decision Priority\n\nChecks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n\n1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HARD STOPS\n\nHard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n\n### Max Iterations Reached\n\n```\nif len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n  return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n```\n\nThe loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n\n### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n\n```\nif coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n  if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n    if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n      return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n```\n\nTriggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n\nIdentifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n\n```\nfunction countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n  count = 0\n  for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n    if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n    if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n    if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n      count += 1\n    else:\n      break\n  return count\n```\n\n**Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n**Status exclusions:**\n- `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n- `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n\nWhen `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n\nThe recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n\nThree independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n\n### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n\nAverages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n  recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n  avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n  rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n```\n\n### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n\nRobust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n  allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n  med = median(allRatios)\n  mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n  noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n  madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\n### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n\nHighest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n\n```\ndimensionStop =\n  dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n  AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n  AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n```\n\nThe latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n\n### Weighted Vote\n\n```\nstopScore = sum(s.weight * (1 if s.stop else 0) for s in signals) / totalWeight\nif stopScore >= 0.60:   // proceed to quality gate evaluation\n```\n\nWeights are redistributed across active signals only. If only 2 signals have enough data, their weights are normalized to sum to 1.0.\n\n### Semantic Convergence Signals\n\nTwo additional signals provide deeper semantic analysis of review iteration quality. These signals are ADDITIONAL to the 3-signal composite vote above and participate in the legal-stop gate evaluation rather than the composite stop-score.\n\n#### semanticNovelty (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how much genuinely new review insight each iteration contributes beyond surface-level overlap with prior findings. Unlike `newFindingsRatio` (which is severity-weighted), `semanticNovelty` evaluates the conceptual novelty of findings independent of severity weighting.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.8-1.0 | Iteration uncovered substantially new defect patterns, architectural concerns, or review angles |\n| 0.4-0.7 | Mix of new review insights and restatements of prior findings |\n| 0.1-0.3 | Mostly refinements or rewordings of previously identified issues |\n| 0.0 | No semantically novel findings detected |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeSemanticNovelty_review(currentFindings, priorCumulativeFindings):\n  newPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings) - extractDefectPatterns(priorCumulativeFindings)\n  totalPatterns = extractDefectPatterns(currentFindings)\n  if len(totalPatterns) == 0: return 0.0\n  return len(newPatterns) / len(totalPatterns)\n```\n\nWhen `semanticNovelty` drops below 0.15 for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations, it provides strong supporting evidence for a legal STOP decision. This signal catches cases where `newFindingsRatio` stays moderate (due to severity weighting of refinements) but the review has exhausted genuinely new defect categories.\n\n#### findingStability (0.0-1.0)\n\nMeasures how stable the cumulative finding set is across iterations. A high stability score means the finding registry is not materially changing between iterations -- findings are not being added, upgraded, downgraded, or invalidated at a significant rate.\n\n| Value | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| 0.9-1.0 | Finding set is highly stable, minimal churn between iterations |\n| 0.6-0.8 | Moderate stability, some findings still evolving |\n| 0.3-0.5 | Active churn, findings being added, merged, or reclassified frequently |\n| 0.0-0.2 | Highly unstable, the review is still in early discovery |\n\nComputation:\n```\nfunction computeFindingStability(currentRegistry, priorRegistry):\n  if priorRegistry is null: return 0.0  // first iteration\n  unchangedFindings = count(f for f in currentRegistry\n    if f.id in priorRegistry and f.severity == priorRegistry[f.id].severity\n    and f.status == priorRegistry[f.id].status)\n  totalFindings = max(len(currentRegistry), len(priorRegistry))\n  if totalFindings == 0: return 1.0\n  return unchangedFindings / totalFindings\n```\n\nConvergence behavior:\n- `findingStability >= 0.85` supports STOP: the finding set has stabilized and further iterations are unlikely to materially change the review outcome.\n- `findingStability < 0.50` prevents STOP: the finding set is still in flux and the review has not reached a stable assessment.\n\n#### Integration with Legal-Stop Gate Bundle\n\nThe two semantic signals integrate with the existing 5-gate legal-stop bundle (Section 6):\n\n1. **findingStability gate** (existing): The existing `findingStability` gate already evaluates rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio. The new `semanticNovelty` signal adds a sub-check:\n   - `semanticNoveltyPlateau`: `semanticNovelty < 0.15` for 2+ consecutive evidence iterations\n   - When this sub-check fails while the existing churn signals pass, the gate records the mismatch as a diagnostic note but does not independently block STOP.\n\n2. **findingStability signal** (new): The `findingStability` metric (0.0-1.0) is surfaced alongside the existing convergence signals. It supports the `findingStability` gate evaluation by providing a registry-level stability measure that complements the ratio-based churn signals.\n\nThe gate passes only when both the existing churn-based checks AND the semantic stability checks agree. When a semantic check fails, the persisted `blocked_stop.gateResults.findingStability` payload includes the semantic signal values.\n\n#### Stop-Decision Trace\n\nThe stop-decision event includes which semantic signals supported or prevented STOP:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stop_decision\",\n  \"semanticSignals\": {\n    \"semanticNovelty\": { \"value\": 0.06, \"consecutiveLow\": 3, \"supportsStop\": true },\n    \"findingStability\": { \"value\": 0.92, \"supportsStop\": true }\n  },\n  \"semanticVerdict\": \"all_support_stop\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n| `semanticVerdict` | Meaning |\n|-------------------|---------|\n| `all_support_stop` | Both semantic signals support stopping |\n| `mixed` | One signal supports stop, the other does not |\n| `all_prevent_stop` | Both semantic signals indicate more work is needed |\n| `insufficient_data` | Not enough iterations to compute semantic signals |\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n| Iterations Completed | Active Signals | Behavior |\n|---------------------|----------------|----------|\n| 1 | Novelty ratio only (weight 1.0) | Very unlikely to stop without later confirmation from rolling churn signals |\n| 2 | Rolling avg + novelty ratio | Two-signal vote, reweighted |\n| 3+ | All three signals | Full composite, most reliable |\n\nSemantic convergence signals (`semanticNovelty`, `findingStability`) require at least 2 evidence iterations to produce meaningful values. They are omitted from legal-stop evaluation when insufficient data exists.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SEVERITY-WEIGHTED RATIO\n\nThe review loop uses `newFindingsRatio` instead of `newInfoRatio`. It weights findings by severity so that critical discoveries count far more than minor suggestions.\n\n### Severity Weights\n\n| Severity | Weight | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| **P0** (Blocker) | 10.0 | Correctness failures, security vulnerabilities, spec contradictions |\n| **P1** (Required) | 5.0 | Degraded behavior, incomplete implementation, missing validation |\n| **P2** (Suggestion) | 1.0 | Style, naming, minor improvements, documentation gaps |\n\n### Computation\n\n```\nSEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 }\nrefinementMultiplier = 0.5\n\nweightedNew       = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in fully_new_findings)\nweightedRefinement = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] * 0.5 for f in refinement_findings)\nweightedTotal     = sum(SEVERITY_WEIGHTS[f.severity] for f in all_findings_this_iteration)\n\nnewFindingsRatio = (weightedNew + weightedRefinement) / weightedTotal\n```\n\n- `fully_new_findings` -- findings not present in any prior iteration (new findingId).\n- `refinement_findings` -- findings that refine or upgrade an existing finding (same root cause, new evidence or severity change).\n- `refinementMultiplier = 0.5` -- refinements count at half weight.\n\n### P0 Override Rule\n\n```\nif ANY new P0 found this iteration:\n  newFindingsRatio = max(calculated, 0.50)\n\nif total_findings == 0:\n  newFindingsRatio = 0.0\n```\n\nA new critical finding always signals significant remaining work. The 0.50 floor prevents premature convergence when critical issues are still being discovered.\n\n---\n\n## 6. LEGAL-STOP GATE BUNDLE\n\n> **GATE MODEL, two naming conventions mapped to one authoritative set.** The authoritative producer is `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`, which emits **9 gates** with the `Gate` suffix: `convergenceGate` / `dimensionCoverageGate` / `p0ResolutionGate` / `evidenceDensityGate` / `hotspotSaturationGate` / `claimAdjudicationGate` / `fixCompletenessReplayGate` / `candidateCoverageGate` / `graphlessFallbackGate`. The §Section-1 event shape (lines 98-119) mirrors this set verbatim and the reducer reads those names verbatim, so treat the event shape as authoritative when writing or reading JSONL state. The §6 table below is the high-level conceptual model and uses descriptive names WITHOUT the `Gate` suffix where one reads more naturally (for example `findingStability` maps to `convergenceGate`); each row carries its event-shape name so the mapping is explicit. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates that pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive. The gate-model drift cluster (LG-0013, LG-0016, LG-0031, LG-0032) was reconciled in `006-gate-model-reconciliation`.\n\nDeep review treats STOP as legal only when the full review-specific gate bundle passes together. Convergence math may request STOP, but the workflow must still evaluate these 9 gates and persist a blocked-stop event when any gate fails.\n\n| Gate (§6 conceptual) | Event-shape name (§Section-1) | Rule | Fail Action |\n|------|------|------|-------------|\n| **findingStability** | `convergenceGate` | Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio must all indicate low-yield review churn | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **dimensionCoverage** | `dimensionCoverageGate` | Every configured review dimension must have been examined at least once, with required traceability coverage stabilized | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **p0Resolution** | `p0ResolutionGate` | No unresolved P0 findings may remain active at stop time | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **evidenceDensity** | `evidenceDensityGate` | Evidence density across active findings must meet the configured threshold | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **hotspotSaturation** | `hotspotSaturationGate` | Review hotspots must be revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| (no §6 counterpart) | `claimAdjudicationGate` | Each new P0/P1 finding must carry a typed adjudication packet, missing or failing packets veto STOP | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **fixCompletenessReplay** | `fixCompletenessReplayGate` | Security-sensitive fix reruns must replay previously closed P0/P1 gates and validate producer/consumer/matrix coverage from the remediation packet | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **candidateCoverage** (v2 rollout) | `candidateCoverageGate` | Search debt must be cleared and every required bug class must have candidate coverage before STOP, passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n| **graphlessFallback** (v2 rollout) | `graphlessFallbackGate` | When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes must carry cited fallback ledger rows, passes trivially when the graph is available | Block STOP, persist `blockedStop` |\n\n### Gate Evaluation\n\n```\nfunction buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage):\n  gateResults = {\n    findingStability: {\n      pass: rollingStop and madStop and state.latestNoveltyRatio <= config.convergenceThreshold,\n      detail: \"Rolling average, MAD noise floor, and novelty ratio are all below stop thresholds.\"\n    },\n    dimensionCoverage: {\n      pass: everyConfiguredDimensionExaminedAtLeastOnce(coverage, config.reviewDimensions) and\n            coverage.requiredProtocolsCovered and\n            coverage.stabilizationPasses >= 1,\n      detail: \"All configured review dimensions have been examined, required traceability protocols are covered, and stabilization has aged enough to stop.\"\n    },\n    p0Resolution: {\n      pass: countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"]) == 0 and state.claimAdjudicationPassed != false,\n      detail: \"No unresolved P0 findings remain and blocker adjudication is complete.\"\n    },\n    evidenceDensity: {\n      pass: computeEvidenceDensity(state.activeFindings) >= config.evidenceDensityThreshold,\n      detail: \"Evidence density meets the configured threshold for active findings.\"\n    },\n    hotspotSaturation: {\n      pass: computeHotspotSaturation(state.hotspots) >= config.hotspotSaturationThreshold,\n      detail: \"Priority hotspots received enough revisits to satisfy saturation.\"\n    },\n    fixCompletenessReplay: {\n      pass: not isSecuritySensitiveFixRerun(state, config) or allRequiredReplayRowsPass(state.reviewReport),\n      detail: \"Security-sensitive fix reruns include closed-gate replay evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage before STOP.\"\n    },\n    candidateCoverage: {\n      pass: not isReviewDepthV2Active(state, config) or (searchDebtCleared(state) and allRequiredBugClassesCovered(state)),\n      detail: \"Search debt is cleared and every required bug class has candidate coverage. Passes trivially when the v2 search path is inactive.\"\n    },\n    graphlessFallback: {\n      pass: state.searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode == \"graph_available\" or allRequiredBugClassesHaveFallbackRows(state),\n      detail: \"When the code graph is unavailable, required bug classes carry cited fallback ledger rows. Passes trivially when the graph is available.\"\n    }\n  }\n\n  blockedBy = [name for name, result in gateResults.items() if not result.pass]\n  return {\n    pass: len(blockedBy) == 0,\n    blockedBy,\n    gateResults\n  }\n```\n\nWhen convergence math returns STOP, invoke `buildReviewLegalStop()`. If it returns `pass: false`, persist a first-class `blocked_stop` event with the failing `blockedBy` gates, the full `gateResults` bundle, a `recoveryStrategy`, and the normal run/timestamp/session lineage fields before overriding the decision to CONTINUE.\n\n### Blocked-Stop Recovery Strategy\n\n| Failed Gate | Recovery Strategy |\n|-------------|-------------------|\n| `findingStability` | Revisit the noisiest recent dimension and reduce novelty by closing obvious follow-up loops before re-checking STOP. |\n| `dimensionCoverage` | Schedule the next uncovered review dimension immediately. |\n| `p0Resolution` | Re-open the active blocker path and verify whether the P0 is real, downgraded, or still unresolved. |\n| `evidenceDensity` | Re-read weakly supported findings and add concrete `file:line` citations before they count toward a stop decision. |\n| `hotspotSaturation` | Revisit undersampled hotspots or adjacent call sites until the saturation heuristic passes. |\n| `fixCompletenessReplay` | Replay prior active or remediated P0/P1 gates, then record producer, consumer, and matrix coverage evidence before re-checking STOP. |\n| `candidateCoverage` | Clear outstanding search debt and run candidate discovery for the missing bug classes before re-checking STOP. |\n| `graphlessFallback` | Add cited fallback ledger rows for the required bug classes, or restore graph availability, before re-checking STOP. |\n\n### Legacy Stop-Reason Mapping\n\nUse this table when replaying old packets or translating older prose/docs into the shared stop contract.\n\n| Legacy label | New `stopReason` | Mapping note |\n|--------------|------------------|--------------|\n| `all_dimensions_clean` | `converged` | Legacy review-specific terminal label, now expressed by the shared enum. |\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` | Legacy convergence-math wording now rolls into shared terminal success. |\n| `all dimensions clean` | `converged` | Old operator-facing prose for the same successful stop. |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` | Legacy machine label for the hard iteration cap. |\n| `max iterations` | `maxIterationsReached` | Old operator-facing hard-stop wording. |\n| `pause sentinel detected` | `userPaused` | Sentinel pause is now a shared user-directed stop reason. |\n| `guard_override` | `blockedStop` | Legacy continue override when a stop vote failed legal gates. |\n| `quality guard failed` | `blockedStop` | Older prose for the same blocked-stop outcome. |\n| `P0 override blocks convergence` | `blockedStop` | Legacy review wording for a stop attempt that was not legal to finalize. |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy recovery trigger label. |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` | Legacy terminal wording for the same recovery path family. |\n| `manual halt` | `manualStop` | Operator-directed halt outside normal pause sentinel flow. |\n\n---\n\n## 7. PROVISIONAL VERDICT\n\nThe provisional verdict is determined from active findings at the time the loop stops. It appears in both the convergence report and the final `review-report.md`.\n\n| Verdict | Condition | Meaning |\n|---------|-----------|---------|\n| **FAIL** | `activeP0 > 0` OR any legal-stop gate fails at terminal stop time | Does not meet quality standards. Blocks release. |\n| **CONDITIONAL** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 > 0` | Meets threshold but has required fixes before release. |\n| **PASS** | `activeP0 == 0` AND `activeP1 == 0` | Shippable. Set `hasAdvisories: true` when `activeP2 > 0`. |\n\n### Determination\n\n```\nfunction determineVerdict(state, gateResult):\n  activeP0 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P0\"])\n  activeP1 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P1\"])\n  activeP2 = countActiveFindings(state, [\"P2\"])\n\n  if activeP0 > 0 or not gateResult.passed:\n    return { verdict: \"FAIL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n  if activeP1 > 0:\n    return { verdict: \"CONDITIONAL\", nextCommand: \"/speckit:plan\" }\n\n  hasAdvisories = activeP2 > 0\n  return { verdict: \"PASS\", hasAdvisories, nextCommand: \"/create:changelog\" }\n```\n\n### Post-Verdict Routing\n\n| Verdict | Next Step |\n|---------|-----------|\n| FAIL | `/speckit:plan` -- create remediation plan from findings |\n| CONDITIONAL | `/speckit:plan` -- create fix plan for P1 findings |\n| PASS | `/create:changelog` -- record the clean audit |\n\n---\n\n## 8. RECOVERY, REPORTING, AND GRAPH-AWARE CONVERGENCE\n\nStuck-recovery strategies, the convergence report format, and graph-aware review convergence live in `convergence_recovery.md` for navigability.\n\n---\n\n## OPTIMIZER-TUNABLE THRESHOLDS\n\nThe following convergence thresholds are managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). Changes to these fields are proposed through the optimizer's advisory-only promotion gate and reviewed by humans before adoption.\n\n### Tunable Fields (Optimizer-Managed)\n\n| Field | Default | Range | Description |\n|-------|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | 0.01-0.20 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | 1-5 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | 3-20 | Hard iteration ceiling |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | 0.40-0.80 | Weighted stop score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Locked Fields (Not Optimizer-Tunable)\n\nThe following fields are runtime contracts and MUST NOT be modified by the optimizer:\n\n- `stopReason` enum values and semantics\n- `blocked_stop` event structure and gate names\n- Lineage fields (`sessionId`, `lineageMode`, `generation`)\n- Reducer configuration and file protection policies\n- Review dimensions (`reviewDimensions`) and product mode (`mode`)\n\n### Canonical Manifest\n\nThe authoritative registry of tunable vs locked fields is maintained at:\n`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":584,"totalLines":584,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1781719868277,"end":1781719868297}},"id":"prt_ed6c79ff6001VdOCSoCPuQONRu","sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","messageID":"msg_ed6c75a86001qw2iF87z3LK0Ab"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719869303,"sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_bFFWgXA2n0qfkYd6a09rgQBG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n14: \n15: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n26: \n27: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n28: |---------|--------|------|\n29: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n30: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n31: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n32: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n33: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n34: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n35: \n36: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n41: \n42: The registry groups findings into:\n43: \n44: - Active findings.\n45: - Resolved findings.\n46: - Repeated findings.\n47: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n48: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n49: \n50: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n55: \n56: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n57: \n58: Recovery order:\n59: \n60: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n61: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n62: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n63: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n68: \n69: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n70: \n71: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n72: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n73: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n74: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n75: \n76: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n81: \n82: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n83: \n84: ### Two-Tier Match\n85: \n86: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n87:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n88:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n89:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n90:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n91: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n92: \n93: ### Synthesis Behavior\n94: \n95: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n96: \n97: ### Emission Requirement\n98: \n99: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n104: \n105: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n106: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n107: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n108: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":108,"totalLines":108,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781719869288,"end":1781719869302}},"id":"prt_ed6c7a3770013oR2FrMe8tXLey","sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","messageID":"msg_ed6c75a86001qw2iF87z3LK0Ab"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781719870258,"sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_ZeenXNfSXchsIiJ9W61aQfVN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: // MODULE: Memory Index\n3: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: import path from 'path';\n5: import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n6: \n7: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8:    1. CORE AND UTILS IMPORTS\n9: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n10: \n11: import { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\n12: import { INDEX_SCAN_COOLDOWN, DEFAULT_BASE_PATH, BATCH_SIZE } from '../core/config.js';\n13: import { beginMaintenance } from '../lib/storage/maintenance-marker.js';\n14: import { acquireIndexScanLease, completeIndexScanLease, refreshScanLease } from '../core/db-state.js';\n15: import { processBatches, requireDb, toErrorMessage, type RetryErrorResult } from '../utils/index.js';\n16: import { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\n17: import { getCanonicalPathKey } from '../lib/utils/canonical-path.js';\n18: import {\n19:   runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n20:   type TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult,\n21: } from '../lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.js';\n22: \n23: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n24:    2. LIB MODULE IMPORTS\n25: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n26: \n27: import { recordHistory } from '../lib/storage/history.js';\n28: import * as checkpoints from '../lib/storage/checkpoints.js';\n29: import * as memoryParser from '../lib/parsing/memory-parser.js';\n30: import * as embeddings from '../lib/providers/embeddings.js';\n31: import * as incrementalIndex from '../lib/storage/incremental-index.js';\n32: import * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\n33: import * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\n34: import { promoteMetadataEdges } from '../lib/causal/frontmatter-promoter.js';\n35: import { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\n36: import { createStatediffAction } from '../lib/storage/statediff.js';\n37: import { repairIncompleteMarkers } from './save/enrichment-state.js';\n38: import { isMemoryIdempotencyEnabled } from '../lib/storage/idempotency-receipts.js';\n39: import { recordNearDuplicateCheck } from '../lib/storage/near-duplicate.js';\n40: import {\n41:   findConstitutionalFiles,\n42:   findGraphMetadataFiles,\n43:   findSpecDocuments,\n44:   detectSpecLevel,\n45:   type DiscoveryCapExceeded,\n46:   type DiscoveryFileList,\n47: } from './memory-index-discovery.js';\n48: import {\n49:   EMPTY_ALIAS_CONFLICT_SUMMARY,\n50:   createDefaultDivergenceReconcileSummary,\n51:   detectAliasConflictsFromIndex,\n52:   summarizeAliasConflicts,\n53:   runDivergenceReconcileHooks,\n54:   type AliasConflictSummary,\n55:   type DivergenceReconcileSummary,\n56: } from './memory-index-alias.js';\n57: \n58: // Standardized response structure\n59: import { createMCPSuccessResponse, createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\n60: import { requiresGovernedIngest, validateGovernedIngest } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n61: import { recordMaintenanceRun } from '../lib/observability/retrieval-observability.js';\n62: import {\n63:   createJobId,\n64:   createMaintenanceJob,\n65:   setJobState,\n66:   setJobPhase,\n67:   setJobProgress,\n68:   appendJobError,\n69:   completeJob,\n70:   isCancelRequestedFast,\n71: } from '../lib/ops/job-store.js';\n72: \n73: // Shared handler types\n74: import type { MCPResponse, EmbeddingProfile } from './types.js';\n75: import type { StatediffAction } from '../lib/storage/statediff.js';\n76: \n77: // Feature catalog: Workspace scanning and indexing (memory_index_scan)\n78: // Feature catalog: Async ingestion job lifecycle\n79: \n80: \n81: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n82:    4. TYPES\n83: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n84: \n85: interface IndexResult {\n86:   status: string;\n87:   id?: number;\n88:   specFolder?: string;\n89:   title?: string | null;\n90:   error?: string;\n91:   errorDetail?: string;\n92:   [key: string]: unknown;\n93: }\n94: \n95: /** Type guard: distinguishes IndexResult from RetryErrorResult via the 'status' property */\n96: function isIndexResult(result: IndexResult | RetryErrorResult): result is IndexResult {\n97:   return (\n98:     typeof result === 'object' &&\n99:     result !== null &&\n100:     typeof (result as { status?: unknown }).status === 'string' &&\n101:     !('retries_failed' in result)\n102:   );\n103: }\n104: \n105: function emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded(): DiscoveryCapExceeded {\n106:   return { maxNodes: false, depth: false, gitignoreSize: false };\n107: }\n108: \n109: function mergeDiscoveryCapExceeded(...caps: Array<DiscoveryCapExceeded | undefined>): DiscoveryCapExceeded {\n110:   return caps.reduce<DiscoveryCapExceeded>((merged, cap) => ({\n111:     maxNodes: merged.maxNodes || cap?.maxNodes === true,\n112:     depth: merged.depth || cap?.depth === true,\n113:     gitignoreSize: merged.gitignoreSize || cap?.gitignoreSize === true,\n114:   }), emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded());\n115: }\n116: \n117: function discoveryWarnings(files: string[] | DiscoveryFileList): string[] {\n118:   const maybeWarnings = (files as Partial<DiscoveryFileList>).warnings;\n119:   return Array.isArray(maybeWarnings) ? maybeWarnings : [];\n120: }\n121: \n122: function discoveryCaps(files: string[] | DiscoveryFileList): DiscoveryCapExceeded | undefined {\n123:   return (files as Partial<DiscoveryFileList>).capExceeded;\n124: }\n125: \n126: /** Individual file result from a memory index scan. */\n127: interface ScanFileEntry {\n128:   file: string;\n129:   filePath?: string;\n130:   status?: string;\n131:   specFolder?: string;\n132:   id?: number;\n133:   isConstitutional?: boolean;\n134:   error?: string;\n135:   errorDetail?: string;\n136: }\n137: \n138: interface CheckpointRepairReport {\n139:   sentinelPresent: boolean;\n140:   attempted: boolean;\n141:   completed: number;\n142:   failed: number;\n143:   skipped: number;\n144:   cleared: boolean;\n145:   error: string | null;\n146: }\n147: \n148: interface ScanResults {\n149:   scanned: number;\n150:   indexed: number;\n151:   updated: number;\n152:   unchanged: number;\n153:   failed: number;\n154:   deferred: number;\n155:   skipped_mtime: number;\n156:   mtimeUpdates: number;\n157:   staleDeleted: number;\n158:   staleDeleteFailed: number;\n159:   postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: number;\n160:   orphanSwept: number;\n161:   orphanSweepFailed: number;\n162:   orphanSweepScanned: number;\n163:   orphanSweepNextCursor: number | null;\n164:   moveReconciled?: number;\n165:   files: ScanFileEntry[];\n166:   constitutional: {\n167:     found: number;\n168:     indexed: number;\n169:     alreadyIndexed: number;\n170:   };\n171:   incremental: {\n172:     enabled: boolean;\n173:     fast_path_skips: number;\n174:     mtime_changed: number;\n175:     metadataPromoter: {\n176:       processed: number;\n177:       resolved: number;\n178:       inserted: number;\n179:       skippedManual: number;\n180:       staleTombstoned: number;\n181:       staleDeleted: number;\n182:       warnings: number;\n183:     };\n184:   };\n185:   dedup: {\n186:     inputTotal: number;\n187:     uniqueTotal: number;\n188:     duplicatesSkipped: number;\n189:   };\n190:   aliasConflicts: AliasConflictSummary;\n191:   divergenceReconcile: DivergenceReconcileSummary;\n192:   checkpointRepair: CheckpointRepairReport;\n193:   triggerEmbeddingBackfill?: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult;\n194:   warnings: string[];\n195:   capExceeded: DiscoveryCapExceeded;\n196: }\n197: \n198: interface CategorizedFiles {\n199:   toIndex: string[];\n200:   toUpdate: string[];\n201:   toSkip: string[];\n202:   toDelete: string[];\n203: }\n204: \n205: interface ScanKeyOptions {\n206:   spec_folder: string | null;\n207:   force: boolean;\n208:   incremental: boolean;\n209:   include_constitutional: boolean;\n210:   include_spec_docs: boolean;\n211: }\n212: \n213: interface RecordDeleteResult {\n214:   deleted: number;\n215:   failed: number;\n216:   actions: StatediffAction[];\n217: }\n218: \n219: interface OrphanSweepDeleteResult {\n220:   swept: number;\n221:   failed: number;\n222:   scannedRows: number;\n223:   nextCursor: number | null;\n224:   actions: StatediffAction[];\n225: }\n226: \n227: interface OrphanSweepCandidates {\n228:   swept: number;\n229:   nextCursor: number | null;\n230:   scannedRows: number;\n231:   orphanRecordIds?: number[];\n232: }\n233: \n234: const ORPHAN_SWEEP_LIMIT = 200;\n235: \n236: // Scan responsiveness diagnostics. A blocked event loop is the failure mode that\n237: // breaks daemon re-election: it cannot answer a competing launcher's probe, so the\n238: // launcher spawns a second daemon. Sampling timer drift distinguishes a true\n239: // event-loop block from a phase that is merely slow but yields — the two need\n240: // different fixes (chunk-and-yield vs launcher-side probe tolerance).\n241: const LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS = 250;\n242: const LOOP_LAG_WARN_MS = 1000;\n243: \n244: function emptyCheckpointRepairReport(): CheckpointRepairReport {\n245:   return {\n246:     sentinelPresent: false,\n247:     attempted: false,\n248:     completed: 0,\n249:     failed: 0,\n250:     skipped: 0,\n251:     cleared: false,\n252:     error: null,\n253:   };\n254: }\n255: \n256: function runCheckpointNeedsRebuildRepairForScan(): CheckpointRepairReport {\n257:   try {\n258:     const repair = checkpoints.repairNeedsRebuildSentinel(requireDb(), {\n259:       source: 'memory_index_scan',\n260:       actor: 'mcp:memory_index_scan',\n261:     });\n262:     return {\n263:       sentinelPresent: repair.sentinelPresent,\n264:       attempted: repair.attempted,\n265:       completed: repair.summary?.completed.length ?? 0,\n266:       failed: repair.summary?.failed.length ?? 0,\n267:       skipped: repair.summary?.skipped.length ?? 0,\n268:       cleared: repair.cleared,\n269:       error: repair.error,\n270:     };\n271:   } catch (error: unknown) {\n272:     return {\n273:       ...emptyCheckpointRepairReport(),\n274:       sentinelPresent: true,\n275:       attempted: true,\n276:       error: toErrorMessage(error),\n277:     };\n278:   }\n279: }\n280: \n281: function createScanKey(options: ScanKeyOptions): string {\n282:   const normalized = {\n283:     spec_folder: options.spec_folder ?? null,\n284:     force: !!options.force,\n285:     incremental: !!options.incremental,\n286:     include_constitutional: !!options.include_constitutional,\n287:     include_spec_docs: !!options.include_spec_docs,\n288:   };\n289: \n290:   return createHash('sha256')\n291:     .update(JSON.stringify(normalized))\n292:     .digest('hex')\n293:     .slice(0, 16);\n294: }\n295: \n296: interface ScanArgs {\n297:   specFolder?: string | null;\n298:   force?: boolean;\n299:   includeConstitutional?: boolean;\n300:   includeSpecDocs?: boolean;\n301:   incremental?: boolean;\n302:   // Opt-in: run the scan as a background job and return a jobId immediately.\n303:   background?: boolean;\n304:   tenantId?: string;\n305:   userId?: string;\n306:   agentId?: string;\n307:   sessionId?: string;\n308:   provenanceSource?: string;\n309:   provenanceActor?: string;\n310:   governedAt?: string;\n311:   retentionPolicy?: 'keep' | 'ephemeral';\n312:   deleteAfter?: string;\n313: }\n314: \n315: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n316:    5. SHARED INDEXING LOGIC\n317: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n318: \n319: import { indexMemoryFile } from './memory-save.js';\n320: import type { GovernanceDecision } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\n321: import type { WriteProvenanceContext } from '../lib/storage/write-provenance.js';\n322: \n323: /** Index a single memory file, delegating to the shared indexMemoryFile logic */\n324: async function indexSingleFile(\n325:   filePath: string,\n326:   force: boolean = false,\n327:   options?: {\n328:     qualityGateMode?: 'enforce' | 'warn-only';\n329:     fromScan?: boolean;\n330:     asyncEmbedding?: boolean;\n331:     governance?: GovernanceDecision;\n332:     provenance?: WriteProvenanceContext;\n333:   },\n334: ): Promise<IndexResult> {\n335:   return indexMemoryFile(filePath, {\n336:     force,\n337:     qualityGateMode: options?.qualityGateMode,\n338:     fromScan: options?.fromScan,\n339:     asyncEmbedding: options?.asyncEmbedding,\n340:     governance: options?.governance,\n341:     provenance: options?.provenance,\n342:   });\n343: }\n344: \n345: /* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n346:    6. MEMORY INDEX SCAN HANDLER\n347: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n348: \n349: // Hooks let a background runner observe cancellation and report phase/progress.\n350: // On the synchronous path every hook is undefined, so behavior is identical.\n351: interface ScanRunContext {\n352:   isCancelled?: () => boolean;\n353:   onPhase?: (phase: string) => void;\n354:   onProgress?: (progress: { processed: number; total: number }) => void;\n355: }\n356: \n357: // Pull the envelope.data field back out of an MCP response so status can echo it.\n358: function extractEnvelopeData(response: MCPResponse): unknown {\n359:   try {\n360:     const text = (response as { content?: Array<{ text?: string }> })?.content?.[0]?.text;\n361:     if (typeof text !== 'string') return null;\n362:     const parsed = JSON.parse(text) as { data?: unknown };\n363:     return parsed?.data ?? null;\n364:   } catch (_error: unknown) {\n365:     return null;\n366:   }\n367: }\n368: \n369: // Persisted payload for debugging: scan shape only, no governance identifiers.\n370: function redactScanArgs(args: ScanArgs): Record<string, unknown> {\n371:   return {\n372:     specFolder: args.specFolder ?? null,\n373:     force: !!args.force,\n374:     includeConstitutional: args.includeConstitutional !== false,\n375:     includeSpecDocs: args.includeSpecDocs !== false,\n376:     incremental: args.incremental !== false,\n377:     background: true,\n378:   };\n379: }\n380: \n381: function cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey: string): MCPResponse {\n382:   return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n383:     tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n384:     summary: 'Index scan cancelled before completion',\n385:     data: { status: 'cancelled', cancelled: true, scanKey },\n386:     hints: ['The scan was cancelled via memory_index_scan_cancel'],\n387:   });\n388: }\n389: \n390: /** Run the full memory_index_scan operation. Hooks are no-ops on the synchronous path. */\n391: async function runIndexScan(args: ScanArgs, ctx: ScanRunContext = {}): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n392:   await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_index_scan');\n393:   const restoreBarrier = checkpoints.getRestoreBarrierStatus();\n394:   if (restoreBarrier) {\n395:     recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', { status: 'error' });\n396:     return createMCPErrorResponse({\n397:       tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n398:       error: restoreBarrier.message,\n399:       code: restoreBarrier.code,\n400:       recovery: {\n401:         hint: 'Retry memory_index_scan after checkpoint_restore maintenance completes.',\n402:         actions: ['Wait for the restore to finish', 'Retry the index scan'],\n403:         severity: 'warning',\n404:       },\n405:     });\n406:   }\n407: \n408:   const {\n409:     specFolder: spec_folder = null,\n410:     force = false,\n411:     includeConstitutional: include_constitutional = true,\n412:     includeSpecDocs: include_spec_docs = true,\n413:     incremental = true\n414:   } = args;\n415:   const scanKey = createScanKey({\n416:     spec_folder,\n417:     force,\n418:     incremental,\n419:     include_constitutional,\n420:     include_spec_docs,\n421:   });\n422:   const governedIngest = requiresGovernedIngest(args);\n423:   const governanceDecision = validateGovernedIngest(args);\n424:   if (!governanceDecision.allowed) {\n425:     throw new Error(`Governed ingest rejected: ${governanceDecision.issues.join('; ')}`);\n426:   }\n427: \n428:   // Pre-flight dimension check\n429:   try {\n430:     const profile: EmbeddingProfile | null = embeddings.getEmbeddingProfile();\n431:     if (profile) {\n432:       console.error(`[memory_index_scan] Using embedding provider: ${profile.provider}, model: ${profile.model}, dimension: ${profile.dim}`);\n433:     }\n434:   } catch (dimCheckError: unknown) {\n435:     const message = toErrorMessage(dimCheckError);\n436:     console.warn('[memory_index_scan] Could not verify embedding dimension:', message);\n437:   }\n438: \n439:   await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n440: \n441:   // Atomic scan lease check.\n442:   // Reserve scan_started_at up front to avoid check-then-set race windows.\n443:   const now = Date.now();\n444:   const lease = await acquireIndexScanLease({\n445:     now,\n446:     cooldownMs: INDEX_SCAN_COOLDOWN,\n447:   });\n448:   if (!lease.acquired) {\n449:     let message: string;\n450:     if (lease.reason === 'lease_active') {\n451:       message = 'A scan is already in progress; this call coalesced onto it.';\n452:     } else if (lease.reason === 'contention') {\n453:       message = 'The index DB is briefly locked by another writer; retry shortly.';\n454:     } else {\n455:       message = 'A scan recently completed; this call coalesced onto the recent scan window.';\n456:     }\n457:     recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', {\n458:       status: 'coalesced',\n459:       counts: { waitSeconds: lease.waitSeconds },\n460:       staleCandidates: 0,\n461:     });\n462:     return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n463:       tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n464:       summary: message,\n465:       data: {\n466:         success: true,\n467:         coalesced: true,\n468:         status: 'coalesced',\n469:         reason: lease.reason,\n470:         scanKey,\n471:         waitSeconds: lease.waitSeconds,\n472:         nextPollAfterMs: lease.waitSeconds * 1000,\n473:         message,\n474:       },\n475:       hints: [message],\n476:     });\n477:   }\n478: \n479:   let scanLeaseReleased = false;\n480:   const releaseScanLease = async (): Promise<void> => {\n481:     if (scanLeaseReleased) return;\n482:     scanLeaseReleased = true;\n483:     await completeIndexScanLease(Date.now());\n484:   };\n485: \n486:   const checkpointRepair = runCheckpointNeedsRebuildRepairForScan();\n487: \n488:   // Keep the scan lease alive for the full duration of a long, multi-batch scan.\n489:   // processBatches() runs all batches sequentially and may exceed the lease expiry\n490:   // window (each batch waits on embedding/API latency). Without a periodic refresh\n491:   // the lease can expire mid-scan, letting a concurrent caller treat it as stale and\n492:   // launch a second parallel scan. Refresh well inside the expiry window (a third of\n493:   // it) so a single missed beat never lets the lease lapse. .unref() keeps the timer\n494:   // from holding the event loop open at shutdown; finally clears it before release.\n495:   const leaseExpiryMs = lease.leaseExpiryMs;\n496:   const leaseHeartbeatMs = Math.max(10000, Math.floor(leaseExpiryMs / 3));\n497:   let leaseHeartbeat: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n498: \n499:   // Background scans pass an onPhase hook; the synchronous foreground path does not.\n500:   // Gate diagnostics on it so the synchronous path's behavior stays identical.\n501:   const instrument = typeof ctx.onPhase === 'function';\n502:   let loopLagTimer: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n503:   let maxLoopLagMs = 0;\n504: \n505:   try {\n506:   leaseHeartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n507:     refreshScanLease();\n508:   }, leaseHeartbeatMs);\n509:   leaseHeartbeat.unref?.();\n510: \n511:   if (instrument) {\n512:     let loopLagExpectedAt = Date.now() + LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS;\n513:     loopLagTimer = setInterval(() => {\n514:       const sampledAt = Date.now();\n515:       const lag = sampledAt - loopLagExpectedAt;\n516:       loopLagExpectedAt = sampledAt + LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS;\n517:       if (lag > maxLoopLagMs) maxLoopLagMs = lag;\n518:       if (lag > LOOP_LAG_WARN_MS) {\n519:         // A late sample means the loop was blocked since the prior tick; logged\n520:         // adjacent to the phase=... line of whatever phase just ran, so the daemon\n521:         // log timeline fingers the blocking phase.\n522:         console.error(`[memory-index-scan] event-loop blocked ~${lag}ms between samples`);\n523:       }\n524:     }, LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS);\n525:     loopLagTimer.unref?.();\n526:   }\n527: \n528:   if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n529:     await releaseScanLease();\n530:     return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n531:   }\n532:   ctx.onPhase?.('discovering');\n533: \n534:   const workspacePath: string = DEFAULT_BASE_PATH;\n535: \n536:   const constitutionalFiles: string[] = include_constitutional ? findConstitutionalFiles(workspacePath) : [];\n537:   const specDocFiles = include_spec_docs\n538:     ? findSpecDocuments(workspacePath, { specFolder: spec_folder })\n539:     : Object.assign([], { warnings: [], capExceeded: emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded() }) as DiscoveryFileList;\n540:   const graphMetadataFiles = include_spec_docs\n541:     ? findGraphMetadataFiles(workspacePath, { specFolder: spec_folder })\n542:     : Object.assign([], { warnings: [], capExceeded: emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded() }) as DiscoveryFileList;\n543:   const walkerWarnings = [\n544:     ...discoveryWarnings(specDocFiles),\n545:     ...discoveryWarnings(graphMetadataFiles),\n546:   ];\n547:   const walkerCapExceeded = mergeDiscoveryCapExceeded(\n548:     discoveryCaps(specDocFiles),\n549:     discoveryCaps(graphMetadataFiles),\n550:   );\n551: \n552:   const canonicalKeyCache = new Map<string, string>();\n553:   const getCachedKey = (filePath: string): string => {\n554:     const cached = canonicalKeyCache.get(filePath);\n555:     if (cached) {\n556:       return cached;\n557:     }\n558: \n559:     const canonicalKey = getCanonicalPathKey(filePath);\n560:     canonicalKeyCache.set(filePath, canonicalKey);\n561:     return canonicalKey;\n562:   };\n563: \n564:   const mergedFiles = [...constitutionalFiles, ...specDocFiles, ...graphMetadataFiles];\n565:   const specDocKeySet = new Set(specDocFiles.map((f) => getCachedKey(f)));\n566:   const seenCanonicalFiles = new Set<string>();\n567:   const files: string[] = [];\n568: \n569:   for (const filePath of mergedFiles) {\n570:     const canonicalKey = getCachedKey(filePath);\n571:     if (seenCanonicalFiles.has(canonicalKey)) {\n572:       continue;\n573:     }\n574:     seenCanonicalFiles.add(canonicalKey);\n575:     files.push(filePath);\n576:   }\n577: \n578:   const dedupDuplicatesSkipped = mergedFiles.length - files.length;\n579:   if (dedupDuplicatesSkipped > 0) {\n580:     console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Canonical dedup skipped ${dedupDuplicatesSkipped} alias path(s) (${mergedFiles.length} -> ${files.length})`);\n581:   }\n582: \n583:   const deleteIndexedRecordIds = (recordIds: number[]): RecordDeleteResult => {\n584:     if (recordIds.length === 0) {\n585:       return { deleted: 0, failed: 0, actions: [] };\n586:     }\n587: \n588:     let deleted = 0;\n589:     let failed = 0;\n590:     const actions: StatediffAction[] = [];\n591: \n592:     for (const staleRecordId of recordIds) {\n593:       try {\n594:         const database = vectorIndex.getDb();\n595:         const staleSnapshot = database?.prepare(\n596:           'SELECT spec_folder, file_path FROM memory_index WHERE id = ?'\n597:         ).get(staleRecordId) as { spec_folder?: string | null; file_path?: string | null } | undefined;\n598: \n599:         if (database) {\n600:           causalEdges.init(database);\n601:           causalEdges.deleteEdgesForMemory(String(staleRecordId), {\n602:             reason: 'memory_index stale record cleanup',\n603:             command: 'memory-index.deleteIndexedRecordIds',\n604:             restoreContext: {\n605:               memoryId: staleRecordId,\n606:               specFolder: staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n607:               filePath: staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n608:             },\n609:           });\n610:         }\n611: \n612:         if (vectorIndex.deleteMemory(staleRecordId)) {\n613:           deleted++;\n614:           actions.push(createStatediffAction('delete', {\n615:             target: 'memory_index',\n616:             key: String(staleRecordId),\n617:             sourceOperation: 'scan',\n618:             oldStateHash: null,\n619:             newStateHash: null,\n620:             metadata: {\n621:               filePath: staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n622:               specFolder: staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n623:             },\n624:           }));\n625:           // Record DELETE history only after confirmed deletion.\n626:           try {\n627:             recordHistory(\n628:               staleRecordId,\n629:               'DELETE',\n630:               staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n631:               null,\n632:               'mcp:memory_index_scan',\n633:               staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n634:             );\n635:           } catch (_histErr: unknown) {\n636:             // History recording is best-effort\n637:           }\n638:         } else {\n639:           failed++;\n640:         }\n641:       } catch (_error: unknown) {\n642:         failed++;\n643:       }\n644:     }\n645: \n646:     return { deleted, failed, actions };\n647:   };\n648: \n649:   const deleteStaleIndexedRecords = (paths: string[]): RecordDeleteResult => {\n650:     if (paths.length === 0) {\n651:       return { deleted: 0, failed: 0, actions: [] };\n652:     }\n653: \n654:     return deleteIndexedRecordIds(incrementalIndex.listIndexedRecordIdsForDeletedPaths(paths));\n655:   };\n656: \n657:   const runGlobalOrphanSweep = (): OrphanSweepDeleteResult => {\n658:     if (!('sweepOrphanIndexRows' in incrementalIndex)) {\n659:       return { swept: 0, failed: 0, scannedRows: 0, nextCursor: null, actions: [] };\n660:     }\n661: \n662:     const sweepOrphanIndexRows = (incrementalIndex as {\n663:       sweepOrphanIndexRows?: (options?: { limit?: number; cursor?: number }) => OrphanSweepCandidates;\n664:     }).sweepOrphanIndexRows;\n665: \n666:     if (typeof sweepOrphanIndexRows !== 'function') {\n667:       return { swept: 0, failed: 0, scannedRows: 0, nextCursor: null, actions: [] };\n668:     }\n669: \n670:     const sweep = sweepOrphanIndexRows({ limit: ORPHAN_SWEEP_LIMIT });\n671:     const deleteResult = deleteIndexedRecordIds(sweep.orphanRecordIds ?? []);\n672:     return {\n673:       swept: deleteResult.deleted,\n674:       failed: deleteResult.failed,\n675:       scannedRows: sweep.scannedRows,\n676:       nextCursor: sweep.nextCursor,\n677:       actions: deleteResult.actions,\n678:     };\n679:   };\n680: \n681:   const runScanInvalidationHooks = (context: Record<string, unknown>, actions: readonly StatediffAction[]): void => {\n682:     try {\n683:       runPostMutationHooks('scan', { ...context, statediffActions: actions });\n684:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n685:       console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Post-mutation invalidation failed:', toErrorMessage(error));\n686:     }\n687:   };\n688: \n689:   const triggerBackfillChangedRows = (result: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult): boolean => (\n690:     result.readyRows > 0 || result.failedRows > 0 || result.pendingRows > 0\n691:   );\n692: \n693:   const createTriggerBackfillAction = (result: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult): StatediffAction => createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n694:     target: 'memory_index',\n695:     key: 'trigger-embedding-backfill',\n696:     sourceOperation: 'scan',\n697:     metadata: {\n698:       readyRows: result.readyRows,\n699:       failedRows: result.failedRows,\n700:       pendingRows: result.pendingRows,\n701:     },\n702:   });\n703: \n704:   const runScanHygieneSubscribers = (actions: readonly StatediffAction[]): void => {\n705:     if (actions.length === 0) {\n706:       return;\n707:     }\n708:     results.aliasConflicts = detectAliasConflictsFromIndex();\n709:     results.divergenceReconcile = runDivergenceReconcileHooks(results.aliasConflicts);\n710:   };\n711: \n712:   const runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill = async (): Promise<number> => {\n713:     try {\n714:       const repairResult = await repairIncompleteMarkers(\n715:         { database: requireDb(), plannerMode: 'full-auto' },\n716:         { limit: BATCH_SIZE },\n717:       );\n718:       if (repairResult.failed > 0) {\n719:         console.warn(`[memory-index-scan] Post-insert enrichment repair left ${repairResult.failed} failed marker(s)`);\n720:       }\n721:       return repairResult.repaired;\n722:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n723:       console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Post-insert enrichment repair skipped:', toErrorMessage(error));\n724:       return 0;\n725:     }\n726:   };\n727: \n728:   const runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill = async (): Promise<number> => {\n729:     if (!isMemoryIdempotencyEnabled()) {\n730:       return 0;\n731:     }\n732:     try {\n733:       const database = requireDb();\n734:       const rows = database.prepare(`\n735:         SELECT id, spec_folder, title, content_text, content_hash,\n736:                tenant_id, user_id, agent_id, session_id\n737:         FROM memory_index\n738:         WHERE parent_id IS NULL\n739:           AND embedding_status = 'success'\n740:           AND content_text IS NOT NULL\n741:           AND (last_dedup_checked_at IS NULL OR updated_at > last_dedup_checked_at)\n742:         ORDER BY id ASC\n743:         LIMIT ?\n744:       `).all(BATCH_SIZE) as Array<{\n745:         id: number;\n746:         spec_folder: string;\n747:         title: string | null;\n748:         content_text: string;\n749:         content_hash: string | null;\n750:         tenant_id: string | null;\n751:         user_id: string | null;\n752:         agent_id: string | null;\n753:         session_id: string | null;\n754:       }>;\n755:       let repaired = 0;\n756:       for (const row of rows) {\n757:         try {\n758:           const embeddingInput = row.title ? `${row.title}\\n\\n${row.content_text}` : row.content_text;\n759:           const embedding = await embeddings.generateDocumentEmbedding(embeddingInput);\n760:           recordNearDuplicateCheck({\n761:             database,\n762:             memoryId: row.id,\n763:             specFolder: row.spec_folder,\n764:             contentHash: row.content_hash,\n765:             embedding,\n766:             scope: {\n767:               tenantId: row.tenant_id,\n768:               userId: row.user_id,\n769:               agentId: row.agent_id,\n770:               sessionId: row.session_id,\n771:             },\n772:           });\n773:           repaired++;\n774:         } catch (error: unknown) {\n775:           console.warn(`[memory-index-scan] Near-duplicate repair skipped for memory ${row.id}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`);\n776:         }\n777:       }\n778:       return repaired;\n779:     } catch (error: unknown) {\n780:       console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Near-duplicate repair skipped:', toErrorMessage(error));\n781:       return 0;\n782:     }\n783:   };\n784: \n785:   if (files.length === 0) {\n786:     let staleDeleted = 0;\n787:     let staleDeleteFailed = 0;\n788:     const orphanSweepResult = runGlobalOrphanSweep();\n789:     const postInsertEnrichmentRepaired = await runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill();\n790:     await runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill();\n791: \n792:     if (incremental && !force) {\n793:       const categorized: CategorizedFiles = incrementalIndex.categorizeFilesForIndexing([]);\n794:       const staleDeleteResult = deleteStaleIndexedRecords(categorized.toDelete);\n795:       staleDeleted = staleDeleteResult.deleted;\n796:       staleDeleteFailed = staleDeleteResult.failed;\n797:       if (staleDeleted > 0) {\n798:         runScanInvalidationHooks({ staleDeleted, staleDeleteFailed, operation: 'stale-delete' }, staleDeleteResult.actions);\n799:       }\n800:     }\n801: \n802:     const triggerEmbeddingBackfill = await runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill(requireDb(), {\n803:       isCancelled: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false,\n804:     });\n805: \n806:     if (orphanSweepResult.swept > 0) {\n807:       runScanInvalidationHooks({\n808:         orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n809:         orphanSweepFailed: orphanSweepResult.failed,\n810:         operation: 'orphan-sweep',\n811:       }, orphanSweepResult.actions);\n812:     }\n813:     if (postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0) {\n814:       runScanInvalidationHooks({\n815:         postInsertEnrichmentRepaired,\n816:         operation: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n817:       }, [createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n818:         target: 'graph_edge',\n819:         key: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n820:         sourceOperation: 'scan',\n821:         metadata: { postInsertEnrichmentRepaired },\n822:       })]);\n823:     }\n824:     if (triggerBackfillChangedRows(triggerEmbeddingBackfill)) {\n825:       runScanInvalidationHooks({\n826:         triggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n827:         operation: 'trigger-embedding-backfill',\n828:       }, [createTriggerBackfillAction(triggerEmbeddingBackfill)]);\n829:     }\n830: \n831:     recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', {\n832:       status: 'success',\n833:       counts: {\n834:         scanned: 0,\n835:         indexed: 0,\n836:         updated: 0,\n837:         unchanged: 0,\n838:         failed: 0,\n839:         staleDeleted,\n840:         staleDeleteFailed,\n841:         orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n842:       },\n843:       staleCandidates: staleDeleted + staleDeleteFailed,\n844:     });\n845:     await releaseScanLease();\n846:     return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n847:       tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n848:       summary: 'No memory files found',\n849:       data: {\n850:         status: 'complete',\n851:         scanKey,\n852:         scanned: 0,\n853:         indexed: 0,\n854:         updated: 0,\n855:         unchanged: 0,\n856:         failed: 0,\n857:         staleDeleted,\n858:         staleDeleteFailed,\n859:         postInsertEnrichmentRepaired,\n860:         triggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n861:         orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n862:         orphanSweepFailed: orphanSweepResult.failed,\n863:         orphanSweepScanned: orphanSweepResult.scannedRows,\n864:         orphanSweepNextCursor: orphanSweepResult.nextCursor,\n865:         checkpointRepair,\n866:         warnings: walkerWarnings,\n867:         capExceeded: walkerCapExceeded,\n868:       },\n869:       hints: [\n870:         ...(staleDeleted > 0 ? [`Removed ${staleDeleted} stale index record(s) for deleted files`] : []),\n871:         ...(postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0 ? [`Repaired ${postInsertEnrichmentRepaired} incomplete post-insert enrichment marker(s)`] : []),\n872:         ...(triggerEmbeddingBackfill.readyRows > 0 ? [`Backfilled ${triggerEmbeddingBackfill.readyRows} trigger embedding row(s)`] : []),\n873:         ...(triggerEmbeddingBackfill.failedRows > 0 ? [`${triggerEmbeddingBackfill.failedRows} trigger embedding row(s) failed backfill`] : []),\n874:         ...(orphanSweepResult.swept > 0 ? [`Swept ${orphanSweepResult.swept} orphan index record(s)`] : []),\n875:         ...(orphanSweepResult.failed > 0 ? [`${orphanSweepResult.failed} orphan index record(s) could not be removed`] : []),\n876:         ...(checkpointRepair.cleared ? [`Cleared checkpoint derived rebuild sentinel after repairing ${checkpointRepair.completed} step(s)`] : []),\n877:         ...(checkpointRepair.attempted && !checkpointRepair.cleared ? ['Checkpoint derived rebuild repair did not complete; sentinel retained'] : []),\n878:         ...(checkpointRepair.error ? [`Checkpoint derived rebuild repair error: ${checkpointRepair.error}`] : []),\n879:         'Indexable files are canonical spec documents under specs/**/ (spec.md, plan.md, decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, handover.md, etc.)',\n880:         'Constitutional files go in .opencode/skills/*/constitutional/'\n881:       ]\n882:     });\n883:   }\n884: \n885:   const constitutionalSet = new Set(constitutionalFiles.map((filePath) => getCachedKey(filePath)));\n886: \n887:   const results: ScanResults = {\n888:     scanned: files.length,\n889:     indexed: 0,\n890:     updated: 0,\n891:     unchanged: 0,\n892:     failed: 0,\n893:     deferred: 0,\n894:     skipped_mtime: 0,\n895:     mtimeUpdates: 0,\n896:     staleDeleted: 0,\n897:     staleDeleteFailed: 0,\n898:     postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: 0,\n899:     orphanSwept: 0,\n900:     orphanSweepFailed: 0,\n901:     orphanSweepScanned: 0,\n902:     orphanSweepNextCursor: null,\n903:     files: [],\n904:     constitutional: {\n905:       found: constitutionalFiles.length,\n906:       indexed: 0,\n907:       alreadyIndexed: 0\n908:     },\n909:     incremental: {\n910:       enabled: incremental && !force,\n911:       fast_path_skips: 0,\n912:       mtime_changed: 0,\n913:       metadataPromoter: {\n914:         processed: 0,\n915:         resolved: 0,\n916:         inserted: 0,\n917:         skippedManual: 0,\n918:         staleTombstoned: 0,\n919:         staleDeleted: 0,\n920:         warnings: 0,\n921:       }\n922:     },\n923:     dedup: {\n924:       inputTotal: mergedFiles.length,\n925:       uniqueTotal: files.length,\n926:       duplicatesSkipped: dedupDuplicatesSkipped,\n927:     },\n928:     aliasConflicts: { ...EMPTY_ALIAS_CONFLICT_SUMMARY },\n929:     divergenceReconcile: createDefaultDivergenceReconcileSummary(),\n930:     checkpointRepair,\n931:     warnings: walkerWarnings,\n932:     capExceeded: walkerCapExceeded,\n933:   };\n934:   const scanAppliedActions: StatediffAction[] = [];\n935: \n936:   let filesToIndex: string[] = files;\n937:   let filesToDelete: string[] = [];\n938: \n939:   if (incremental && !force) {\n940:     const startCategorize = Date.now();\n941:     const categorized: CategorizedFiles = incrementalIndex.categorizeFilesForIndexing(files);\n942: \n943:     filesToIndex = [...categorized.toIndex, ...categorized.toUpdate];\n944:     filesToDelete = categorized.toDelete;\n945: \n946:     results.unchanged = categorized.toSkip.length;\n947:     results.skipped_mtime = categorized.toSkip.length;\n948:     results.incremental.fast_path_skips = categorized.toSkip.length;\n949:     results.incremental.mtime_changed = categorized.toUpdate.length;\n950: \n951:     for (const unchangedPath of categorized.toSkip) {\n952:       if (constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(unchangedPath))) {\n953:         results.constitutional.alreadyIndexed++;\n954:       }\n955:     }\n956: \n957:     const categorizeTime = Date.now() - startCategorize;\n958:     console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Incremental mode: ${filesToIndex.length}/${files.length} files need indexing (categorized in ${categorizeTime}ms)`);\n959:     console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Fast-path skips: ${results.incremental.fast_path_skips}, Mtime changed: ${results.incremental.mtime_changed}`);\n960:   }\n961: \n962:   // Attempt move reconciliation before full delete+reindex cycle.\n963:   // Pairs a vanished path with a new path by grandparent dir + basename (a sibling folder\n964:   // rename), gated by the new folder still carrying a packet_id and by DB uniqueness +\n965:   // stored-document_type cross-checks; the matched row is updated in place.\n966:   if (filesToDelete.length > 0 && filesToIndex.length > 0) {\n967:     const moveResult = incrementalIndex.reconcileMoves(filesToDelete, filesToIndex);\n968:     if (moveResult.reconciled.length > 0) {\n969:       results.moveReconciled = moveResult.reconciled.length;\n970:       filesToDelete = moveResult.filteredToDelete;\n971:       filesToIndex = moveResult.filteredToIndex;\n972:       console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Move reconciled ${moveResult.reconciled.length} path(s) in place`);\n973:     }\n974:   }\n975: \n976:   const plannedScanActions = [\n977:     ...filesToIndex.map((filePath) => createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n978:       target: 'memory_index',\n979:       key: getCachedKey(filePath),\n980:       sourceOperation: 'scan',\n981:       metadata: { filePath },\n982:     })),\n983:     ...filesToDelete.map((filePath) => createStatediffAction('delete', {\n984:       target: 'memory_index',\n985:       key: getCachedKey(filePath),\n986:       sourceOperation: 'scan',\n987:       metadata: { filePath },\n988:     })),\n989:   ];\n990:   if (plannedScanActions.length > 0) {\n991:     console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Statediff plan: ${plannedScanActions.length} action(s) before scan writes`);\n992:   }\n993: \n994:   // Track successfully indexed files for post-indexing mtime update.\n995:   // SAFETY INVARIANT: mtime markers are updated ONLY after indexing succeeds.\n996:   // Failed files keep their old mtime so shouldReindex() returns 'modified'\n997:   // Or 'new' on the next scan, ensuring automatic retry. Moving this update\n998:   // Before indexing would cause silent data loss — a failed file would be\n999:   // Marked \"already indexed\" and permanently skipped.\n1000:   const successfullyIndexedFiles: string[] = [];\n1001:   const scanBatchSize = BATCH_SIZE;\n1002: \n1003:   ctx.onPhase?.('indexing');\n1004:   ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: 0, total: filesToIndex.length });\n1005: \n1006:   if (filesToIndex.length > 0) {\n1007:     let processedInScan = 0;\n1008:     const batchResults = await processBatches(filesToIndex, async (filePath: string) => {\n1009:       // Cancellation is checked between files (mirrors ingest). A cancelled file is\n1010:       // returned as a no-op so its mtime is never bumped, preserving retry on re-run.\n1011:       if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n1012:         return { status: 'cancelled' } as IndexResult;\n1013:       }\n1014:       const isSpecDoc = specDocKeySet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n1015:       // Constitutional markdown is policy text, not evidence-bearing memory.\n1016:       // It does not carry primary-evidence sections or ANCHOR tags by design, so the\n1017:       // strict sufficiency gate would always reject it. Treat constitutional files like\n1018:       // spec docs and pass them through warn-only mode so they index against the same\n1019:       // pipeline without the document-evidence requirements.\n1020:       const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n1021:       // During force reindex, use warn-only for all files — the goal is to index\n1022:       // everything that has valid frontmatter, not to enforce template contracts on\n1023:       // older files created before current templates were established.\n1024:       const useWarnOnly = force || isSpecDoc || isConstitutional;\n1025:       const indexResult = await indexSingleFile(filePath, force, {\n1026:         ...(useWarnOnly ? { qualityGateMode: 'warn-only' as const } : {}),\n1027:         fromScan: true,\n1028:         asyncEmbedding: true,\n1029:         governance: governedIngest ? governanceDecision : undefined,\n1030:       });\n1031:       processedInScan += 1;\n1032:       ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: processedInScan, total: filesToIndex.length });\n1033:       return indexResult;\n1034:     }, scanBatchSize, undefined, { shouldAbort: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false });\n1035: \n1036:     for (let i = 0; i < batchResults.length; i++) {\n1037:       const result = batchResults[i];\n1038:       const filePath = filesToIndex[i];\n1039:       const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n1040: \n1041:       if (result.error) {\n1042:         results.failed++;\n1043:         results.files.push({\n1044:           file: path.basename(filePath),\n1045:           filePath,\n1046:           status: 'failed',\n1047:           error: result.error,\n1048:           errorDetail: result.errorDetail\n1049:         });\n1050:       } else if (isIndexResult(result)) {\n1051:         const isSuccessfulStatus =\n1052:           result.status === 'success' ||\n1053:           result.status === 'indexed' ||\n1054:           result.status === 'updated' ||\n1055:           result.status === 'unchanged' ||\n1056:           result.status === 'reinforced' ||\n1057:           result.status === 'duplicate' ||\n1058:           result.status === 'deferred';\n1059:         if (!isSuccessfulStatus) {\n1060:           results.failed++;\n1061:         }\n1062: \n1063:         if (result.status === 'indexed') {\n1064:           results.indexed++;\n1065:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1066:           scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('insert', {\n1067:             target: 'memory_index',\n1068:             key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n1069:             sourceOperation: 'scan',\n1070:             metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n1071:           }));\n1072:         } else if (result.status === 'updated') {\n1073:           results.updated++;\n1074:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1075:           scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n1076:             target: 'memory_index',\n1077:             key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n1078:             sourceOperation: 'scan',\n1079:             metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n1080:           }));\n1081:         } else if (result.status === 'unchanged') {\n1082:           results.unchanged++;\n1083:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1084:         } else if (result.status === 'reinforced') {\n1085:           results.updated++;\n1086:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1087:           scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n1088:             target: 'memory_index',\n1089:             key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n1090:             sourceOperation: 'scan',\n1091:             metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n1092:           }));\n1093:         } else if (result.status === 'duplicate') {\n1094:           results.unchanged++;\n1095:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1096:         } else if (result.status === 'deferred') {\n1097:           results.indexed++;\n1098:           results.deferred++;\n1099:           successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n1100:           scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('insert', {\n1101:             target: 'memory_index',\n1102:             key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n1103:             sourceOperation: 'scan',\n1104:             metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n1105:           }));\n1106:         }\n1107: \n1108:         if (isConstitutional) {\n1109:           if (result.status === 'indexed') {\n1110:             results.constitutional.indexed++;\n1111:           } else if (result.status === 'unchanged') {\n1112:             results.constitutional.alreadyIndexed++;\n1113:           }\n1114:         }\n1115: \n1116:         if (result.status !== 'unchanged') {\n1117:           const rejectionDetail = !isSuccessfulStatus\n1118:             ? {\n1119:                 ...(typeof result.rejectionCode === 'string' && result.rejectionCode.length > 0\n1120:                   ? { rejectionCode: result.rejectionCode }\n1121:                   : {}),\n1122:                 ...(typeof result.rejectionReason === 'string' && result.rejectionReason.length > 0\n1123:                   ? { rejectionReason: result.rejectionReason }\n1124:                   : (typeof result.message === 'string' && result.message.length > 0\n1125:                     ? { rejectionReason: result.message }\n1126:                     : {})),\n1127:                 ...(typeof result.error === 'string' && result.error.length > 0\n1128:                   ? { error: result.error }\n1129:                   : {}),\n1130:               }\n1131:             : {};\n1132: \n1133:           results.files.push({\n1134:             file: path.basename(filePath),\n1135:             filePath,\n1136:             specFolder: result.specFolder,\n1137:             status: result.status,\n1138:             id: result.id,\n1139:             isConstitutional,\n1140:             ...rejectionDetail,\n1141:           });\n1142:         }\n1143:       } else {\n1144:         results.failed++;\n1145:         results.files.push({\n1146:           file: path.basename(filePath),\n1147:           filePath,\n1148:           status: 'failed',\n1149:           error: 'Unexpected batch result shape',\n1150:           errorDetail: JSON.stringify(result),\n1151:         });\n1152:       }\n1153:     }\n1154:   }\n1155: \n1156:   // Update mtimes ONLY for successfully indexed files, not before indexing.\n1157:   // Failed files keep their old mtime so they are retried on next scan.\n1158:   // This is the ONLY place where scan-triggered mtime updates occur.\n1159:   // See also: indexMemoryFile() sets file_mtime_ms within its DB transaction,\n1160:   // Which rolls back atomically on failure — a complementary safety mechanism.\n1161:   if (successfullyIndexedFiles.length > 0) {\n1162:     const mtimeUpdateResult = incrementalIndex.batchUpdateMtimes(successfullyIndexedFiles);\n1163:     results.mtimeUpdates = mtimeUpdateResult.updated;\n1164:   }\n1165: \n1166:   if (include_spec_docs) {\n1167:     const database = requireDb();\n1168:     let promoterYieldCount = 0;\n1169:     for (const fileResult of results.files) {\n1170:       // This sweep is synchronous SQLite over EVERY indexed row. On a force scan\n1171:       // that is the whole corpus, so without a periodic macrotask yield the event\n1172:       // loop is starved for the duration and no IPC (status, cancel, health,\n1173:       // search) can be serviced. Yield and re-check cancellation between rows; the\n1174:       // yield lands between self-contained promoteMetadataEdges transactions, never\n1175:       // inside one, so atomicity on the shared connection is preserved.\n1176:       if (++promoterYieldCount % 200 === 0) {\n1177:         if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n1178:           return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n1179:         }\n1180:         await new Promise<void>((resolve) => setImmediate(resolve));\n1181:       }\n1182:       if (!fileResult.id || !fileResult.filePath || fileResult.status === 'failed') {\n1183:         continue;\n1184:       }\n1185:       try {\n1186:         const promotion = promoteMetadataEdges(database, {\n1187:           memoryId: fileResult.id,\n1188:           filePath: fileResult.filePath,\n1189:         });\n1190:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.processed += promotion.processed;\n1191:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.resolved += promotion.resolved;\n1192:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.inserted += promotion.inserted;\n1193:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.skippedManual += promotion.skippedManual;\n1194:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.staleTombstoned += promotion.staleTombstoned;\n1195:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.staleDeleted += promotion.staleDeleted;\n1196:         results.incremental.metadataPromoter.warnings += promotion.warnings.length;\n1197:         for (const warning of promotion.warnings) {\n1198:           results.warnings.push(`Metadata edge promoter: ${warning.field} ${warning.reference}: ${warning.message}`);\n1199:         }\n1200:       } catch (error: unknown) {\n1201:         results.warnings.push(`Metadata edge promoter failed for ${fileResult.filePath}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`);\n1202:       }\n1203:     }\n1204:   }\n1205: \n1206:   if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n1207:     return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n1208:   }\n1209:   ctx.onPhase?.('post-processing');\n1210: \n1211:   if (filesToDelete.length > 0) {\n1212:     if (results.failed === 0) {\n1213:       const staleDeleteResult = deleteStaleIndexedRecords(filesToDelete);\n1214:       results.staleDeleted = staleDeleteResult.deleted;\n1215:       results.staleDeleteFailed = staleDeleteResult.failed;\n1216:       scanAppliedActions.push(...staleDeleteResult.actions);\n1217:     } else {\n1218:       console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Deferring stale cleanup because one or more replacement files failed to index');\n1219:     }\n1220:   }\n1221: \n1222:   // Time each un-yielded tail phase: because these phases do not yield, their\n1223:   // wall-clock equals their event-loop-block duration, so this pinpoints a blocking\n1224:   // phase when read alongside the event-loop lag sampler. Entering a phase also fires\n1225:   // onPhase, which refreshes the busy marker — giving each phase a full TTL ahead.\n1226:   const timedPhase = async <T>(phase: string, fn: () => Promise<T> | T): Promise<T> => {\n1227:     ctx.onPhase?.(phase);\n1228:     if (!instrument) {\n1229:       return await fn();\n1230:     }\n1231:     const startedAt = Date.now();\n1232:     try {\n1233:       return await fn();\n1234:     } finally {\n1235:       console.error(`[memory-index-scan] phase=${phase} ms=${Date.now() - startedAt}`);\n1236:     }\n1237:   };\n1238: \n1239:   const orphanSweepResult = await timedPhase('orphan-sweep', () => runGlobalOrphanSweep());\n1240:   results.orphanSwept = orphanSweepResult.swept;\n1241:   results.orphanSweepFailed = orphanSweepResult.failed;\n1242:   results.orphanSweepScanned = orphanSweepResult.scannedRows;\n1243:   results.orphanSweepNextCursor = orphanSweepResult.nextCursor;\n1244:   scanAppliedActions.push(...orphanSweepResult.actions);\n1245: \n1246:   results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired = await timedPhase('enrichment-repair', () => runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill());\n1247:   if (results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0) {\n1248:     scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n1249:       target: 'graph_edge',\n1250:       key: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n1251:       sourceOperation: 'scan',\n1252:       metadata: { postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired },\n1253:     }));\n1254:   }\n1255: \n1256:   results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill = await timedPhase('trigger-backfill', () =>\n1257:     runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill(requireDb(), { isCancelled: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false }));\n1258:   if (triggerBackfillChangedRows(results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill)) {\n1259:     scanAppliedActions.push(createTriggerBackfillAction(results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill));\n1260:   }\n1261:   await timedPhase('near-dup-repair', () => runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill());\n1262: \n1263:   // Create causal chains between spec folder documents.\n1264:   // Includes deferred indexing outcomes and incremental single-file updates.\n1265:   if (include_spec_docs) {\n1266:     try {\n1267:       // Determine which spec folders had spec document changes in this scan.\n1268:       // We use parsed document type (not basename) to avoid false positives\n1269:       // From memory/plan.md or similar filenames.\n1270:       const affectedSpecFolders = new Set<string>();\n1271:       for (const fileResult of results.files) {\n1272:         if (!fileResult.specFolder || fileResult.status === 'failed') {\n1273:           continue;\n1274:         }\n1275: \n1276:         if (!fileResult.filePath) {\n1277:           continue;\n1278:         }\n1279: \n1280:         const docType = memoryParser.extractDocumentType(fileResult.filePath);\n1281:         if (\n1282:           docType !== 'memory' &&\n1283:           docType !== 'constitutional'\n1284:         ) {\n1285:           affectedSpecFolders.add(fileResult.specFolder);\n1286:         }\n1287:       }\n1288: \n1289:       if (affectedSpecFolders.size > 0) {\n1290:         const database = requireDb();\n1291:         const { createSpecDocumentChain, init: initCausalEdges } = await import('../lib/storage/causal-edges.js');\n1292:         initCausalEdges(database);\n1293: \n1294:         // Build full per-folder document map from DB (not just this scan's files).\n1295:         const selectDocIds = database.prepare(`\n1296:           SELECT document_type, MAX(id) AS id\n1297:           FROM memory_index\n1298:           WHERE spec_folder = ?\n1299:             AND document_type IN ('spec', 'plan', 'tasks', 'checklist', 'decision_record', 'implementation_summary', 'research', 'handover', 'graph_metadata')\n1300:           GROUP BY document_type\n1301:         `);\n1302: \n1303:         let chainsCreated = 0;\n1304:         let foldersProcessed = 0;\n1305:         let chainYieldCount = 0;\n1306: \n1307:         for (const folder of affectedSpecFolders) {\n1308:           // Per-folder synchronous DB work; yield + cancel-check between folders so a\n1309:           // large affected set cannot block the event loop (same rationale as the\n1310:           // metadata-edge sweep above).\n1311:           if (++chainYieldCount % 50 === 0) {\n1312:             if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n1313:               return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n1314:             }\n1315:             await new Promise<void>((resolve) => setImmediate(resolve));\n1316:           }\n1317:           const rows = selectDocIds.all(folder) as Array<{ document_type: string; id: number }>;\n1318:           const docIds: Record<string, number> = {};\n1319: \n1320:           for (const row of rows) {\n1321:             if (row.document_type && typeof row.id === 'number') {\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1321. Use offset=1322 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Index\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. CORE AND UTILS IMPORTS\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { INDEX_SCAN_COOLDOWN, DEFAULT_BASE_PATH, BATCH_SIZE } from '../core/config.js';\nimport { beginMaintenance } from '../lib/storage/maintenance-marker.js';\nimport { acquireIndexScanLease, completeIndexScanLease, refreshScanLease } from '../core/db-state.js';\nimport { processBatches, requireDb, toErrorMessage, type RetryErrorResult } from '../utils/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport { getCanonicalPathKey } from '../lib/utils/canonical-path.js';\nimport {\n  runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n  type TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult,","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","text":"// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Memory Index\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. CORE AND UTILS IMPORTS\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { checkDatabaseUpdated } from '../core/index.js';\nimport { INDEX_SCAN_COOLDOWN, DEFAULT_BASE_PATH, BATCH_SIZE } from '../core/config.js';\nimport { beginMaintenance } from '../lib/storage/maintenance-marker.js';\nimport { acquireIndexScanLease, completeIndexScanLease, refreshScanLease } from '../core/db-state.js';\nimport { processBatches, requireDb, toErrorMessage, type RetryErrorResult } from '../utils/index.js';\nimport { ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized } from '../lib/runtime/memory-runtime-guard.js';\nimport { getCanonicalPathKey } from '../lib/utils/canonical-path.js';\nimport {\n  runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n  type TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult,\n} from '../lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.js';\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   2. LIB MODULE IMPORTS\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { recordHistory } from '../lib/storage/history.js';\nimport * as checkpoints from '../lib/storage/checkpoints.js';\nimport * as memoryParser from '../lib/parsing/memory-parser.js';\nimport * as embeddings from '../lib/providers/embeddings.js';\nimport * as incrementalIndex from '../lib/storage/incremental-index.js';\nimport * as causalEdges from '../lib/storage/causal-edges.js';\nimport * as vectorIndex from '../lib/search/vector-index.js';\nimport { promoteMetadataEdges } from '../lib/causal/frontmatter-promoter.js';\nimport { runPostMutationHooks } from './mutation-hooks.js';\nimport { createStatediffAction } from '../lib/storage/statediff.js';\nimport { repairIncompleteMarkers } from './save/enrichment-state.js';\nimport { isMemoryIdempotencyEnabled } from '../lib/storage/idempotency-receipts.js';\nimport { recordNearDuplicateCheck } from '../lib/storage/near-duplicate.js';\nimport {\n  findConstitutionalFiles,\n  findGraphMetadataFiles,\n  findSpecDocuments,\n  detectSpecLevel,\n  type DiscoveryCapExceeded,\n  type DiscoveryFileList,\n} from './memory-index-discovery.js';\nimport {\n  EMPTY_ALIAS_CONFLICT_SUMMARY,\n  createDefaultDivergenceReconcileSummary,\n  detectAliasConflictsFromIndex,\n  summarizeAliasConflicts,\n  runDivergenceReconcileHooks,\n  type AliasConflictSummary,\n  type DivergenceReconcileSummary,\n} from './memory-index-alias.js';\n\n// Standardized response structure\nimport { createMCPSuccessResponse, createMCPErrorResponse } from '../lib/response/envelope.js';\nimport { requiresGovernedIngest, validateGovernedIngest } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\nimport { recordMaintenanceRun } from '../lib/observability/retrieval-observability.js';\nimport {\n  createJobId,\n  createMaintenanceJob,\n  setJobState,\n  setJobPhase,\n  setJobProgress,\n  appendJobError,\n  completeJob,\n  isCancelRequestedFast,\n} from '../lib/ops/job-store.js';\n\n// Shared handler types\nimport type { MCPResponse, EmbeddingProfile } from './types.js';\nimport type { StatediffAction } from '../lib/storage/statediff.js';\n\n// Feature catalog: Workspace scanning and indexing (memory_index_scan)\n// Feature catalog: Async ingestion job lifecycle\n\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   4. TYPES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\ninterface IndexResult {\n  status: string;\n  id?: number;\n  specFolder?: string;\n  title?: string | null;\n  error?: string;\n  errorDetail?: string;\n  [key: string]: unknown;\n}\n\n/** Type guard: distinguishes IndexResult from RetryErrorResult via the 'status' property */\nfunction isIndexResult(result: IndexResult | RetryErrorResult): result is IndexResult {\n  return (\n    typeof result === 'object' &&\n    result !== null &&\n    typeof (result as { status?: unknown }).status === 'string' &&\n    !('retries_failed' in result)\n  );\n}\n\nfunction emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded(): DiscoveryCapExceeded {\n  return { maxNodes: false, depth: false, gitignoreSize: false };\n}\n\nfunction mergeDiscoveryCapExceeded(...caps: Array<DiscoveryCapExceeded | undefined>): DiscoveryCapExceeded {\n  return caps.reduce<DiscoveryCapExceeded>((merged, cap) => ({\n    maxNodes: merged.maxNodes || cap?.maxNodes === true,\n    depth: merged.depth || cap?.depth === true,\n    gitignoreSize: merged.gitignoreSize || cap?.gitignoreSize === true,\n  }), emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded());\n}\n\nfunction discoveryWarnings(files: string[] | DiscoveryFileList): string[] {\n  const maybeWarnings = (files as Partial<DiscoveryFileList>).warnings;\n  return Array.isArray(maybeWarnings) ? maybeWarnings : [];\n}\n\nfunction discoveryCaps(files: string[] | DiscoveryFileList): DiscoveryCapExceeded | undefined {\n  return (files as Partial<DiscoveryFileList>).capExceeded;\n}\n\n/** Individual file result from a memory index scan. */\ninterface ScanFileEntry {\n  file: string;\n  filePath?: string;\n  status?: string;\n  specFolder?: string;\n  id?: number;\n  isConstitutional?: boolean;\n  error?: string;\n  errorDetail?: string;\n}\n\ninterface CheckpointRepairReport {\n  sentinelPresent: boolean;\n  attempted: boolean;\n  completed: number;\n  failed: number;\n  skipped: number;\n  cleared: boolean;\n  error: string | null;\n}\n\ninterface ScanResults {\n  scanned: number;\n  indexed: number;\n  updated: number;\n  unchanged: number;\n  failed: number;\n  deferred: number;\n  skipped_mtime: number;\n  mtimeUpdates: number;\n  staleDeleted: number;\n  staleDeleteFailed: number;\n  postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: number;\n  orphanSwept: number;\n  orphanSweepFailed: number;\n  orphanSweepScanned: number;\n  orphanSweepNextCursor: number | null;\n  moveReconciled?: number;\n  files: ScanFileEntry[];\n  constitutional: {\n    found: number;\n    indexed: number;\n    alreadyIndexed: number;\n  };\n  incremental: {\n    enabled: boolean;\n    fast_path_skips: number;\n    mtime_changed: number;\n    metadataPromoter: {\n      processed: number;\n      resolved: number;\n      inserted: number;\n      skippedManual: number;\n      staleTombstoned: number;\n      staleDeleted: number;\n      warnings: number;\n    };\n  };\n  dedup: {\n    inputTotal: number;\n    uniqueTotal: number;\n    duplicatesSkipped: number;\n  };\n  aliasConflicts: AliasConflictSummary;\n  divergenceReconcile: DivergenceReconcileSummary;\n  checkpointRepair: CheckpointRepairReport;\n  triggerEmbeddingBackfill?: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult;\n  warnings: string[];\n  capExceeded: DiscoveryCapExceeded;\n}\n\ninterface CategorizedFiles {\n  toIndex: string[];\n  toUpdate: string[];\n  toSkip: string[];\n  toDelete: string[];\n}\n\ninterface ScanKeyOptions {\n  spec_folder: string | null;\n  force: boolean;\n  incremental: boolean;\n  include_constitutional: boolean;\n  include_spec_docs: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface RecordDeleteResult {\n  deleted: number;\n  failed: number;\n  actions: StatediffAction[];\n}\n\ninterface OrphanSweepDeleteResult {\n  swept: number;\n  failed: number;\n  scannedRows: number;\n  nextCursor: number | null;\n  actions: StatediffAction[];\n}\n\ninterface OrphanSweepCandidates {\n  swept: number;\n  nextCursor: number | null;\n  scannedRows: number;\n  orphanRecordIds?: number[];\n}\n\nconst ORPHAN_SWEEP_LIMIT = 200;\n\n// Scan responsiveness diagnostics. A blocked event loop is the failure mode that\n// breaks daemon re-election: it cannot answer a competing launcher's probe, so the\n// launcher spawns a second daemon. Sampling timer drift distinguishes a true\n// event-loop block from a phase that is merely slow but yields — the two need\n// different fixes (chunk-and-yield vs launcher-side probe tolerance).\nconst LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS = 250;\nconst LOOP_LAG_WARN_MS = 1000;\n\nfunction emptyCheckpointRepairReport(): CheckpointRepairReport {\n  return {\n    sentinelPresent: false,\n    attempted: false,\n    completed: 0,\n    failed: 0,\n    skipped: 0,\n    cleared: false,\n    error: null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction runCheckpointNeedsRebuildRepairForScan(): CheckpointRepairReport {\n  try {\n    const repair = checkpoints.repairNeedsRebuildSentinel(requireDb(), {\n      source: 'memory_index_scan',\n      actor: 'mcp:memory_index_scan',\n    });\n    return {\n      sentinelPresent: repair.sentinelPresent,\n      attempted: repair.attempted,\n      completed: repair.summary?.completed.length ?? 0,\n      failed: repair.summary?.failed.length ?? 0,\n      skipped: repair.summary?.skipped.length ?? 0,\n      cleared: repair.cleared,\n      error: repair.error,\n    };\n  } catch (error: unknown) {\n    return {\n      ...emptyCheckpointRepairReport(),\n      sentinelPresent: true,\n      attempted: true,\n      error: toErrorMessage(error),\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nfunction createScanKey(options: ScanKeyOptions): string {\n  const normalized = {\n    spec_folder: options.spec_folder ?? null,\n    force: !!options.force,\n    incremental: !!options.incremental,\n    include_constitutional: !!options.include_constitutional,\n    include_spec_docs: !!options.include_spec_docs,\n  };\n\n  return createHash('sha256')\n    .update(JSON.stringify(normalized))\n    .digest('hex')\n    .slice(0, 16);\n}\n\ninterface ScanArgs {\n  specFolder?: string | null;\n  force?: boolean;\n  includeConstitutional?: boolean;\n  includeSpecDocs?: boolean;\n  incremental?: boolean;\n  // Opt-in: run the scan as a background job and return a jobId immediately.\n  background?: boolean;\n  tenantId?: string;\n  userId?: string;\n  agentId?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  provenanceSource?: string;\n  provenanceActor?: string;\n  governedAt?: string;\n  retentionPolicy?: 'keep' | 'ephemeral';\n  deleteAfter?: string;\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   5. SHARED INDEXING LOGIC\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\nimport { indexMemoryFile } from './memory-save.js';\nimport type { GovernanceDecision } from '../lib/governance/scope-governance.js';\nimport type { WriteProvenanceContext } from '../lib/storage/write-provenance.js';\n\n/** Index a single memory file, delegating to the shared indexMemoryFile logic */\nasync function indexSingleFile(\n  filePath: string,\n  force: boolean = false,\n  options?: {\n    qualityGateMode?: 'enforce' | 'warn-only';\n    fromScan?: boolean;\n    asyncEmbedding?: boolean;\n    governance?: GovernanceDecision;\n    provenance?: WriteProvenanceContext;\n  },\n): Promise<IndexResult> {\n  return indexMemoryFile(filePath, {\n    force,\n    qualityGateMode: options?.qualityGateMode,\n    fromScan: options?.fromScan,\n    asyncEmbedding: options?.asyncEmbedding,\n    governance: options?.governance,\n    provenance: options?.provenance,\n  });\n}\n\n/* ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   6. MEMORY INDEX SCAN HANDLER\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n\n// Hooks let a background runner observe cancellation and report phase/progress.\n// On the synchronous path every hook is undefined, so behavior is identical.\ninterface ScanRunContext {\n  isCancelled?: () => boolean;\n  onPhase?: (phase: string) => void;\n  onProgress?: (progress: { processed: number; total: number }) => void;\n}\n\n// Pull the envelope.data field back out of an MCP response so status can echo it.\nfunction extractEnvelopeData(response: MCPResponse): unknown {\n  try {\n    const text = (response as { content?: Array<{ text?: string }> })?.content?.[0]?.text;\n    if (typeof text !== 'string') return null;\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(text) as { data?: unknown };\n    return parsed?.data ?? null;\n  } catch (_error: unknown) {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n// Persisted payload for debugging: scan shape only, no governance identifiers.\nfunction redactScanArgs(args: ScanArgs): Record<string, unknown> {\n  return {\n    specFolder: args.specFolder ?? null,\n    force: !!args.force,\n    includeConstitutional: args.includeConstitutional !== false,\n    includeSpecDocs: args.includeSpecDocs !== false,\n    incremental: args.incremental !== false,\n    background: true,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey: string): MCPResponse {\n  return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n    tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n    summary: 'Index scan cancelled before completion',\n    data: { status: 'cancelled', cancelled: true, scanKey },\n    hints: ['The scan was cancelled via memory_index_scan_cancel'],\n  });\n}\n\n/** Run the full memory_index_scan operation. Hooks are no-ops on the synchronous path. */\nasync function runIndexScan(args: ScanArgs, ctx: ScanRunContext = {}): Promise<MCPResponse> {\n  await ensureMemoryRuntimeInitialized('handler:memory_index_scan');\n  const restoreBarrier = checkpoints.getRestoreBarrierStatus();\n  if (restoreBarrier) {\n    recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', { status: 'error' });\n    return createMCPErrorResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n      error: restoreBarrier.message,\n      code: restoreBarrier.code,\n      recovery: {\n        hint: 'Retry memory_index_scan after checkpoint_restore maintenance completes.',\n        actions: ['Wait for the restore to finish', 'Retry the index scan'],\n        severity: 'warning',\n      },\n    });\n  }\n\n  const {\n    specFolder: spec_folder = null,\n    force = false,\n    includeConstitutional: include_constitutional = true,\n    includeSpecDocs: include_spec_docs = true,\n    incremental = true\n  } = args;\n  const scanKey = createScanKey({\n    spec_folder,\n    force,\n    incremental,\n    include_constitutional,\n    include_spec_docs,\n  });\n  const governedIngest = requiresGovernedIngest(args);\n  const governanceDecision = validateGovernedIngest(args);\n  if (!governanceDecision.allowed) {\n    throw new Error(`Governed ingest rejected: ${governanceDecision.issues.join('; ')}`);\n  }\n\n  // Pre-flight dimension check\n  try {\n    const profile: EmbeddingProfile | null = embeddings.getEmbeddingProfile();\n    if (profile) {\n      console.error(`[memory_index_scan] Using embedding provider: ${profile.provider}, model: ${profile.model}, dimension: ${profile.dim}`);\n    }\n  } catch (dimCheckError: unknown) {\n    const message = toErrorMessage(dimCheckError);\n    console.warn('[memory_index_scan] Could not verify embedding dimension:', message);\n  }\n\n  await checkDatabaseUpdated();\n\n  // Atomic scan lease check.\n  // Reserve scan_started_at up front to avoid check-then-set race windows.\n  const now = Date.now();\n  const lease = await acquireIndexScanLease({\n    now,\n    cooldownMs: INDEX_SCAN_COOLDOWN,\n  });\n  if (!lease.acquired) {\n    let message: string;\n    if (lease.reason === 'lease_active') {\n      message = 'A scan is already in progress; this call coalesced onto it.';\n    } else if (lease.reason === 'contention') {\n      message = 'The index DB is briefly locked by another writer; retry shortly.';\n    } else {\n      message = 'A scan recently completed; this call coalesced onto the recent scan window.';\n    }\n    recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', {\n      status: 'coalesced',\n      counts: { waitSeconds: lease.waitSeconds },\n      staleCandidates: 0,\n    });\n    return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n      summary: message,\n      data: {\n        success: true,\n        coalesced: true,\n        status: 'coalesced',\n        reason: lease.reason,\n        scanKey,\n        waitSeconds: lease.waitSeconds,\n        nextPollAfterMs: lease.waitSeconds * 1000,\n        message,\n      },\n      hints: [message],\n    });\n  }\n\n  let scanLeaseReleased = false;\n  const releaseScanLease = async (): Promise<void> => {\n    if (scanLeaseReleased) return;\n    scanLeaseReleased = true;\n    await completeIndexScanLease(Date.now());\n  };\n\n  const checkpointRepair = runCheckpointNeedsRebuildRepairForScan();\n\n  // Keep the scan lease alive for the full duration of a long, multi-batch scan.\n  // processBatches() runs all batches sequentially and may exceed the lease expiry\n  // window (each batch waits on embedding/API latency). Without a periodic refresh\n  // the lease can expire mid-scan, letting a concurrent caller treat it as stale and\n  // launch a second parallel scan. Refresh well inside the expiry window (a third of\n  // it) so a single missed beat never lets the lease lapse. .unref() keeps the timer\n  // from holding the event loop open at shutdown; finally clears it before release.\n  const leaseExpiryMs = lease.leaseExpiryMs;\n  const leaseHeartbeatMs = Math.max(10000, Math.floor(leaseExpiryMs / 3));\n  let leaseHeartbeat: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n\n  // Background scans pass an onPhase hook; the synchronous foreground path does not.\n  // Gate diagnostics on it so the synchronous path's behavior stays identical.\n  const instrument = typeof ctx.onPhase === 'function';\n  let loopLagTimer: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n  let maxLoopLagMs = 0;\n\n  try {\n  leaseHeartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n    refreshScanLease();\n  }, leaseHeartbeatMs);\n  leaseHeartbeat.unref?.();\n\n  if (instrument) {\n    let loopLagExpectedAt = Date.now() + LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS;\n    loopLagTimer = setInterval(() => {\n      const sampledAt = Date.now();\n      const lag = sampledAt - loopLagExpectedAt;\n      loopLagExpectedAt = sampledAt + LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS;\n      if (lag > maxLoopLagMs) maxLoopLagMs = lag;\n      if (lag > LOOP_LAG_WARN_MS) {\n        // A late sample means the loop was blocked since the prior tick; logged\n        // adjacent to the phase=... line of whatever phase just ran, so the daemon\n        // log timeline fingers the blocking phase.\n        console.error(`[memory-index-scan] event-loop blocked ~${lag}ms between samples`);\n      }\n    }, LOOP_LAG_SAMPLE_MS);\n    loopLagTimer.unref?.();\n  }\n\n  if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n    await releaseScanLease();\n    return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n  }\n  ctx.onPhase?.('discovering');\n\n  const workspacePath: string = DEFAULT_BASE_PATH;\n\n  const constitutionalFiles: string[] = include_constitutional ? findConstitutionalFiles(workspacePath) : [];\n  const specDocFiles = include_spec_docs\n    ? findSpecDocuments(workspacePath, { specFolder: spec_folder })\n    : Object.assign([], { warnings: [], capExceeded: emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded() }) as DiscoveryFileList;\n  const graphMetadataFiles = include_spec_docs\n    ? findGraphMetadataFiles(workspacePath, { specFolder: spec_folder })\n    : Object.assign([], { warnings: [], capExceeded: emptyDiscoveryCapExceeded() }) as DiscoveryFileList;\n  const walkerWarnings = [\n    ...discoveryWarnings(specDocFiles),\n    ...discoveryWarnings(graphMetadataFiles),\n  ];\n  const walkerCapExceeded = mergeDiscoveryCapExceeded(\n    discoveryCaps(specDocFiles),\n    discoveryCaps(graphMetadataFiles),\n  );\n\n  const canonicalKeyCache = new Map<string, string>();\n  const getCachedKey = (filePath: string): string => {\n    const cached = canonicalKeyCache.get(filePath);\n    if (cached) {\n      return cached;\n    }\n\n    const canonicalKey = getCanonicalPathKey(filePath);\n    canonicalKeyCache.set(filePath, canonicalKey);\n    return canonicalKey;\n  };\n\n  const mergedFiles = [...constitutionalFiles, ...specDocFiles, ...graphMetadataFiles];\n  const specDocKeySet = new Set(specDocFiles.map((f) => getCachedKey(f)));\n  const seenCanonicalFiles = new Set<string>();\n  const files: string[] = [];\n\n  for (const filePath of mergedFiles) {\n    const canonicalKey = getCachedKey(filePath);\n    if (seenCanonicalFiles.has(canonicalKey)) {\n      continue;\n    }\n    seenCanonicalFiles.add(canonicalKey);\n    files.push(filePath);\n  }\n\n  const dedupDuplicatesSkipped = mergedFiles.length - files.length;\n  if (dedupDuplicatesSkipped > 0) {\n    console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Canonical dedup skipped ${dedupDuplicatesSkipped} alias path(s) (${mergedFiles.length} -> ${files.length})`);\n  }\n\n  const deleteIndexedRecordIds = (recordIds: number[]): RecordDeleteResult => {\n    if (recordIds.length === 0) {\n      return { deleted: 0, failed: 0, actions: [] };\n    }\n\n    let deleted = 0;\n    let failed = 0;\n    const actions: StatediffAction[] = [];\n\n    for (const staleRecordId of recordIds) {\n      try {\n        const database = vectorIndex.getDb();\n        const staleSnapshot = database?.prepare(\n          'SELECT spec_folder, file_path FROM memory_index WHERE id = ?'\n        ).get(staleRecordId) as { spec_folder?: string | null; file_path?: string | null } | undefined;\n\n        if (database) {\n          causalEdges.init(database);\n          causalEdges.deleteEdgesForMemory(String(staleRecordId), {\n            reason: 'memory_index stale record cleanup',\n            command: 'memory-index.deleteIndexedRecordIds',\n            restoreContext: {\n              memoryId: staleRecordId,\n              specFolder: staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n              filePath: staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n            },\n          });\n        }\n\n        if (vectorIndex.deleteMemory(staleRecordId)) {\n          deleted++;\n          actions.push(createStatediffAction('delete', {\n            target: 'memory_index',\n            key: String(staleRecordId),\n            sourceOperation: 'scan',\n            oldStateHash: null,\n            newStateHash: null,\n            metadata: {\n              filePath: staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n              specFolder: staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n            },\n          }));\n          // Record DELETE history only after confirmed deletion.\n          try {\n            recordHistory(\n              staleRecordId,\n              'DELETE',\n              staleSnapshot?.file_path ?? null,\n              null,\n              'mcp:memory_index_scan',\n              staleSnapshot?.spec_folder ?? null,\n            );\n          } catch (_histErr: unknown) {\n            // History recording is best-effort\n          }\n        } else {\n          failed++;\n        }\n      } catch (_error: unknown) {\n        failed++;\n      }\n    }\n\n    return { deleted, failed, actions };\n  };\n\n  const deleteStaleIndexedRecords = (paths: string[]): RecordDeleteResult => {\n    if (paths.length === 0) {\n      return { deleted: 0, failed: 0, actions: [] };\n    }\n\n    return deleteIndexedRecordIds(incrementalIndex.listIndexedRecordIdsForDeletedPaths(paths));\n  };\n\n  const runGlobalOrphanSweep = (): OrphanSweepDeleteResult => {\n    if (!('sweepOrphanIndexRows' in incrementalIndex)) {\n      return { swept: 0, failed: 0, scannedRows: 0, nextCursor: null, actions: [] };\n    }\n\n    const sweepOrphanIndexRows = (incrementalIndex as {\n      sweepOrphanIndexRows?: (options?: { limit?: number; cursor?: number }) => OrphanSweepCandidates;\n    }).sweepOrphanIndexRows;\n\n    if (typeof sweepOrphanIndexRows !== 'function') {\n      return { swept: 0, failed: 0, scannedRows: 0, nextCursor: null, actions: [] };\n    }\n\n    const sweep = sweepOrphanIndexRows({ limit: ORPHAN_SWEEP_LIMIT });\n    const deleteResult = deleteIndexedRecordIds(sweep.orphanRecordIds ?? []);\n    return {\n      swept: deleteResult.deleted,\n      failed: deleteResult.failed,\n      scannedRows: sweep.scannedRows,\n      nextCursor: sweep.nextCursor,\n      actions: deleteResult.actions,\n    };\n  };\n\n  const runScanInvalidationHooks = (context: Record<string, unknown>, actions: readonly StatediffAction[]): void => {\n    try {\n      runPostMutationHooks('scan', { ...context, statediffActions: actions });\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Post-mutation invalidation failed:', toErrorMessage(error));\n    }\n  };\n\n  const triggerBackfillChangedRows = (result: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult): boolean => (\n    result.readyRows > 0 || result.failedRows > 0 || result.pendingRows > 0\n  );\n\n  const createTriggerBackfillAction = (result: TriggerEmbeddingBackfillResult): StatediffAction => createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n    target: 'memory_index',\n    key: 'trigger-embedding-backfill',\n    sourceOperation: 'scan',\n    metadata: {\n      readyRows: result.readyRows,\n      failedRows: result.failedRows,\n      pendingRows: result.pendingRows,\n    },\n  });\n\n  const runScanHygieneSubscribers = (actions: readonly StatediffAction[]): void => {\n    if (actions.length === 0) {\n      return;\n    }\n    results.aliasConflicts = detectAliasConflictsFromIndex();\n    results.divergenceReconcile = runDivergenceReconcileHooks(results.aliasConflicts);\n  };\n\n  const runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill = async (): Promise<number> => {\n    try {\n      const repairResult = await repairIncompleteMarkers(\n        { database: requireDb(), plannerMode: 'full-auto' },\n        { limit: BATCH_SIZE },\n      );\n      if (repairResult.failed > 0) {\n        console.warn(`[memory-index-scan] Post-insert enrichment repair left ${repairResult.failed} failed marker(s)`);\n      }\n      return repairResult.repaired;\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Post-insert enrichment repair skipped:', toErrorMessage(error));\n      return 0;\n    }\n  };\n\n  const runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill = async (): Promise<number> => {\n    if (!isMemoryIdempotencyEnabled()) {\n      return 0;\n    }\n    try {\n      const database = requireDb();\n      const rows = database.prepare(`\n        SELECT id, spec_folder, title, content_text, content_hash,\n               tenant_id, user_id, agent_id, session_id\n        FROM memory_index\n        WHERE parent_id IS NULL\n          AND embedding_status = 'success'\n          AND content_text IS NOT NULL\n          AND (last_dedup_checked_at IS NULL OR updated_at > last_dedup_checked_at)\n        ORDER BY id ASC\n        LIMIT ?\n      `).all(BATCH_SIZE) as Array<{\n        id: number;\n        spec_folder: string;\n        title: string | null;\n        content_text: string;\n        content_hash: string | null;\n        tenant_id: string | null;\n        user_id: string | null;\n        agent_id: string | null;\n        session_id: string | null;\n      }>;\n      let repaired = 0;\n      for (const row of rows) {\n        try {\n          const embeddingInput = row.title ? `${row.title}\\n\\n${row.content_text}` : row.content_text;\n          const embedding = await embeddings.generateDocumentEmbedding(embeddingInput);\n          recordNearDuplicateCheck({\n            database,\n            memoryId: row.id,\n            specFolder: row.spec_folder,\n            contentHash: row.content_hash,\n            embedding,\n            scope: {\n              tenantId: row.tenant_id,\n              userId: row.user_id,\n              agentId: row.agent_id,\n              sessionId: row.session_id,\n            },\n          });\n          repaired++;\n        } catch (error: unknown) {\n          console.warn(`[memory-index-scan] Near-duplicate repair skipped for memory ${row.id}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`);\n        }\n      }\n      return repaired;\n    } catch (error: unknown) {\n      console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Near-duplicate repair skipped:', toErrorMessage(error));\n      return 0;\n    }\n  };\n\n  if (files.length === 0) {\n    let staleDeleted = 0;\n    let staleDeleteFailed = 0;\n    const orphanSweepResult = runGlobalOrphanSweep();\n    const postInsertEnrichmentRepaired = await runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill();\n    await runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill();\n\n    if (incremental && !force) {\n      const categorized: CategorizedFiles = incrementalIndex.categorizeFilesForIndexing([]);\n      const staleDeleteResult = deleteStaleIndexedRecords(categorized.toDelete);\n      staleDeleted = staleDeleteResult.deleted;\n      staleDeleteFailed = staleDeleteResult.failed;\n      if (staleDeleted > 0) {\n        runScanInvalidationHooks({ staleDeleted, staleDeleteFailed, operation: 'stale-delete' }, staleDeleteResult.actions);\n      }\n    }\n\n    const triggerEmbeddingBackfill = await runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill(requireDb(), {\n      isCancelled: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false,\n    });\n\n    if (orphanSweepResult.swept > 0) {\n      runScanInvalidationHooks({\n        orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n        orphanSweepFailed: orphanSweepResult.failed,\n        operation: 'orphan-sweep',\n      }, orphanSweepResult.actions);\n    }\n    if (postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0) {\n      runScanInvalidationHooks({\n        postInsertEnrichmentRepaired,\n        operation: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n      }, [createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n        target: 'graph_edge',\n        key: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n        sourceOperation: 'scan',\n        metadata: { postInsertEnrichmentRepaired },\n      })]);\n    }\n    if (triggerBackfillChangedRows(triggerEmbeddingBackfill)) {\n      runScanInvalidationHooks({\n        triggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n        operation: 'trigger-embedding-backfill',\n      }, [createTriggerBackfillAction(triggerEmbeddingBackfill)]);\n    }\n\n    recordMaintenanceRun('memory_index_scan', {\n      status: 'success',\n      counts: {\n        scanned: 0,\n        indexed: 0,\n        updated: 0,\n        unchanged: 0,\n        failed: 0,\n        staleDeleted,\n        staleDeleteFailed,\n        orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n      },\n      staleCandidates: staleDeleted + staleDeleteFailed,\n    });\n    await releaseScanLease();\n    return createMCPSuccessResponse({\n      tool: 'memory_index_scan',\n      summary: 'No memory files found',\n      data: {\n        status: 'complete',\n        scanKey,\n        scanned: 0,\n        indexed: 0,\n        updated: 0,\n        unchanged: 0,\n        failed: 0,\n        staleDeleted,\n        staleDeleteFailed,\n        postInsertEnrichmentRepaired,\n        triggerEmbeddingBackfill,\n        orphanSwept: orphanSweepResult.swept,\n        orphanSweepFailed: orphanSweepResult.failed,\n        orphanSweepScanned: orphanSweepResult.scannedRows,\n        orphanSweepNextCursor: orphanSweepResult.nextCursor,\n        checkpointRepair,\n        warnings: walkerWarnings,\n        capExceeded: walkerCapExceeded,\n      },\n      hints: [\n        ...(staleDeleted > 0 ? [`Removed ${staleDeleted} stale index record(s) for deleted files`] : []),\n        ...(postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0 ? [`Repaired ${postInsertEnrichmentRepaired} incomplete post-insert enrichment marker(s)`] : []),\n        ...(triggerEmbeddingBackfill.readyRows > 0 ? [`Backfilled ${triggerEmbeddingBackfill.readyRows} trigger embedding row(s)`] : []),\n        ...(triggerEmbeddingBackfill.failedRows > 0 ? [`${triggerEmbeddingBackfill.failedRows} trigger embedding row(s) failed backfill`] : []),\n        ...(orphanSweepResult.swept > 0 ? [`Swept ${orphanSweepResult.swept} orphan index record(s)`] : []),\n        ...(orphanSweepResult.failed > 0 ? [`${orphanSweepResult.failed} orphan index record(s) could not be removed`] : []),\n        ...(checkpointRepair.cleared ? [`Cleared checkpoint derived rebuild sentinel after repairing ${checkpointRepair.completed} step(s)`] : []),\n        ...(checkpointRepair.attempted && !checkpointRepair.cleared ? ['Checkpoint derived rebuild repair did not complete; sentinel retained'] : []),\n        ...(checkpointRepair.error ? [`Checkpoint derived rebuild repair error: ${checkpointRepair.error}`] : []),\n        'Indexable files are canonical spec documents under specs/**/ (spec.md, plan.md, decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, handover.md, etc.)',\n        'Constitutional files go in .opencode/skills/*/constitutional/'\n      ]\n    });\n  }\n\n  const constitutionalSet = new Set(constitutionalFiles.map((filePath) => getCachedKey(filePath)));\n\n  const results: ScanResults = {\n    scanned: files.length,\n    indexed: 0,\n    updated: 0,\n    unchanged: 0,\n    failed: 0,\n    deferred: 0,\n    skipped_mtime: 0,\n    mtimeUpdates: 0,\n    staleDeleted: 0,\n    staleDeleteFailed: 0,\n    postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: 0,\n    orphanSwept: 0,\n    orphanSweepFailed: 0,\n    orphanSweepScanned: 0,\n    orphanSweepNextCursor: null,\n    files: [],\n    constitutional: {\n      found: constitutionalFiles.length,\n      indexed: 0,\n      alreadyIndexed: 0\n    },\n    incremental: {\n      enabled: incremental && !force,\n      fast_path_skips: 0,\n      mtime_changed: 0,\n      metadataPromoter: {\n        processed: 0,\n        resolved: 0,\n        inserted: 0,\n        skippedManual: 0,\n        staleTombstoned: 0,\n        staleDeleted: 0,\n        warnings: 0,\n      }\n    },\n    dedup: {\n      inputTotal: mergedFiles.length,\n      uniqueTotal: files.length,\n      duplicatesSkipped: dedupDuplicatesSkipped,\n    },\n    aliasConflicts: { ...EMPTY_ALIAS_CONFLICT_SUMMARY },\n    divergenceReconcile: createDefaultDivergenceReconcileSummary(),\n    checkpointRepair,\n    warnings: walkerWarnings,\n    capExceeded: walkerCapExceeded,\n  };\n  const scanAppliedActions: StatediffAction[] = [];\n\n  let filesToIndex: string[] = files;\n  let filesToDelete: string[] = [];\n\n  if (incremental && !force) {\n    const startCategorize = Date.now();\n    const categorized: CategorizedFiles = incrementalIndex.categorizeFilesForIndexing(files);\n\n    filesToIndex = [...categorized.toIndex, ...categorized.toUpdate];\n    filesToDelete = categorized.toDelete;\n\n    results.unchanged = categorized.toSkip.length;\n    results.skipped_mtime = categorized.toSkip.length;\n    results.incremental.fast_path_skips = categorized.toSkip.length;\n    results.incremental.mtime_changed = categorized.toUpdate.length;\n\n    for (const unchangedPath of categorized.toSkip) {\n      if (constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(unchangedPath))) {\n        results.constitutional.alreadyIndexed++;\n      }\n    }\n\n    const categorizeTime = Date.now() - startCategorize;\n    console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Incremental mode: ${filesToIndex.length}/${files.length} files need indexing (categorized in ${categorizeTime}ms)`);\n    console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Fast-path skips: ${results.incremental.fast_path_skips}, Mtime changed: ${results.incremental.mtime_changed}`);\n  }\n\n  // Attempt move reconciliation before full delete+reindex cycle.\n  // Pairs a vanished path with a new path by grandparent dir + basename (a sibling folder\n  // rename), gated by the new folder still carrying a packet_id and by DB uniqueness +\n  // stored-document_type cross-checks; the matched row is updated in place.\n  if (filesToDelete.length > 0 && filesToIndex.length > 0) {\n    const moveResult = incrementalIndex.reconcileMoves(filesToDelete, filesToIndex);\n    if (moveResult.reconciled.length > 0) {\n      results.moveReconciled = moveResult.reconciled.length;\n      filesToDelete = moveResult.filteredToDelete;\n      filesToIndex = moveResult.filteredToIndex;\n      console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Move reconciled ${moveResult.reconciled.length} path(s) in place`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  const plannedScanActions = [\n    ...filesToIndex.map((filePath) => createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n      target: 'memory_index',\n      key: getCachedKey(filePath),\n      sourceOperation: 'scan',\n      metadata: { filePath },\n    })),\n    ...filesToDelete.map((filePath) => createStatediffAction('delete', {\n      target: 'memory_index',\n      key: getCachedKey(filePath),\n      sourceOperation: 'scan',\n      metadata: { filePath },\n    })),\n  ];\n  if (plannedScanActions.length > 0) {\n    console.error(`[memory-index-scan] Statediff plan: ${plannedScanActions.length} action(s) before scan writes`);\n  }\n\n  // Track successfully indexed files for post-indexing mtime update.\n  // SAFETY INVARIANT: mtime markers are updated ONLY after indexing succeeds.\n  // Failed files keep their old mtime so shouldReindex() returns 'modified'\n  // Or 'new' on the next scan, ensuring automatic retry. Moving this update\n  // Before indexing would cause silent data loss — a failed file would be\n  // Marked \"already indexed\" and permanently skipped.\n  const successfullyIndexedFiles: string[] = [];\n  const scanBatchSize = BATCH_SIZE;\n\n  ctx.onPhase?.('indexing');\n  ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: 0, total: filesToIndex.length });\n\n  if (filesToIndex.length > 0) {\n    let processedInScan = 0;\n    const batchResults = await processBatches(filesToIndex, async (filePath: string) => {\n      // Cancellation is checked between files (mirrors ingest). A cancelled file is\n      // returned as a no-op so its mtime is never bumped, preserving retry on re-run.\n      if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n        return { status: 'cancelled' } as IndexResult;\n      }\n      const isSpecDoc = specDocKeySet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n      // Constitutional markdown is policy text, not evidence-bearing memory.\n      // It does not carry primary-evidence sections or ANCHOR tags by design, so the\n      // strict sufficiency gate would always reject it. Treat constitutional files like\n      // spec docs and pass them through warn-only mode so they index against the same\n      // pipeline without the document-evidence requirements.\n      const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n      // During force reindex, use warn-only for all files — the goal is to index\n      // everything that has valid frontmatter, not to enforce template contracts on\n      // older files created before current templates were established.\n      const useWarnOnly = force || isSpecDoc || isConstitutional;\n      const indexResult = await indexSingleFile(filePath, force, {\n        ...(useWarnOnly ? { qualityGateMode: 'warn-only' as const } : {}),\n        fromScan: true,\n        asyncEmbedding: true,\n        governance: governedIngest ? governanceDecision : undefined,\n      });\n      processedInScan += 1;\n      ctx.onProgress?.({ processed: processedInScan, total: filesToIndex.length });\n      return indexResult;\n    }, scanBatchSize, undefined, { shouldAbort: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false });\n\n    for (let i = 0; i < batchResults.length; i++) {\n      const result = batchResults[i];\n      const filePath = filesToIndex[i];\n      const isConstitutional = constitutionalSet.has(getCachedKey(filePath));\n\n      if (result.error) {\n        results.failed++;\n        results.files.push({\n          file: path.basename(filePath),\n          filePath,\n          status: 'failed',\n          error: result.error,\n          errorDetail: result.errorDetail\n        });\n      } else if (isIndexResult(result)) {\n        const isSuccessfulStatus =\n          result.status === 'success' ||\n          result.status === 'indexed' ||\n          result.status === 'updated' ||\n          result.status === 'unchanged' ||\n          result.status === 'reinforced' ||\n          result.status === 'duplicate' ||\n          result.status === 'deferred';\n        if (!isSuccessfulStatus) {\n          results.failed++;\n        }\n\n        if (result.status === 'indexed') {\n          results.indexed++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n          scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('insert', {\n            target: 'memory_index',\n            key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n            sourceOperation: 'scan',\n            metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n          }));\n        } else if (result.status === 'updated') {\n          results.updated++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n          scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n            target: 'memory_index',\n            key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n            sourceOperation: 'scan',\n            metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n          }));\n        } else if (result.status === 'unchanged') {\n          results.unchanged++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n        } else if (result.status === 'reinforced') {\n          results.updated++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n          scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n            target: 'memory_index',\n            key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n            sourceOperation: 'scan',\n            metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n          }));\n        } else if (result.status === 'duplicate') {\n          results.unchanged++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n        } else if (result.status === 'deferred') {\n          results.indexed++;\n          results.deferred++;\n          successfullyIndexedFiles.push(filePath);\n          scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('insert', {\n            target: 'memory_index',\n            key: String(result.id ?? getCachedKey(filePath)),\n            sourceOperation: 'scan',\n            metadata: { filePath, specFolder: result.specFolder ?? null, status: result.status },\n          }));\n        }\n\n        if (isConstitutional) {\n          if (result.status === 'indexed') {\n            results.constitutional.indexed++;\n          } else if (result.status === 'unchanged') {\n            results.constitutional.alreadyIndexed++;\n          }\n        }\n\n        if (result.status !== 'unchanged') {\n          const rejectionDetail = !isSuccessfulStatus\n            ? {\n                ...(typeof result.rejectionCode === 'string' && result.rejectionCode.length > 0\n                  ? { rejectionCode: result.rejectionCode }\n                  : {}),\n                ...(typeof result.rejectionReason === 'string' && result.rejectionReason.length > 0\n                  ? { rejectionReason: result.rejectionReason }\n                  : (typeof result.message === 'string' && result.message.length > 0\n                    ? { rejectionReason: result.message }\n                    : {})),\n                ...(typeof result.error === 'string' && result.error.length > 0\n                  ? { error: result.error }\n                  : {}),\n              }\n            : {};\n\n          results.files.push({\n            file: path.basename(filePath),\n            filePath,\n            specFolder: result.specFolder,\n            status: result.status,\n            id: result.id,\n            isConstitutional,\n            ...rejectionDetail,\n          });\n        }\n      } else {\n        results.failed++;\n        results.files.push({\n          file: path.basename(filePath),\n          filePath,\n          status: 'failed',\n          error: 'Unexpected batch result shape',\n          errorDetail: JSON.stringify(result),\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Update mtimes ONLY for successfully indexed files, not before indexing.\n  // Failed files keep their old mtime so they are retried on next scan.\n  // This is the ONLY place where scan-triggered mtime updates occur.\n  // See also: indexMemoryFile() sets file_mtime_ms within its DB transaction,\n  // Which rolls back atomically on failure — a complementary safety mechanism.\n  if (successfullyIndexedFiles.length > 0) {\n    const mtimeUpdateResult = incrementalIndex.batchUpdateMtimes(successfullyIndexedFiles);\n    results.mtimeUpdates = mtimeUpdateResult.updated;\n  }\n\n  if (include_spec_docs) {\n    const database = requireDb();\n    let promoterYieldCount = 0;\n    for (const fileResult of results.files) {\n      // This sweep is synchronous SQLite over EVERY indexed row. On a force scan\n      // that is the whole corpus, so without a periodic macrotask yield the event\n      // loop is starved for the duration and no IPC (status, cancel, health,\n      // search) can be serviced. Yield and re-check cancellation between rows; the\n      // yield lands between self-contained promoteMetadataEdges transactions, never\n      // inside one, so atomicity on the shared connection is preserved.\n      if (++promoterYieldCount % 200 === 0) {\n        if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n          return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n        }\n        await new Promise<void>((resolve) => setImmediate(resolve));\n      }\n      if (!fileResult.id || !fileResult.filePath || fileResult.status === 'failed') {\n        continue;\n      }\n      try {\n        const promotion = promoteMetadataEdges(database, {\n          memoryId: fileResult.id,\n          filePath: fileResult.filePath,\n        });\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.processed += promotion.processed;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.resolved += promotion.resolved;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.inserted += promotion.inserted;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.skippedManual += promotion.skippedManual;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.staleTombstoned += promotion.staleTombstoned;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.staleDeleted += promotion.staleDeleted;\n        results.incremental.metadataPromoter.warnings += promotion.warnings.length;\n        for (const warning of promotion.warnings) {\n          results.warnings.push(`Metadata edge promoter: ${warning.field} ${warning.reference}: ${warning.message}`);\n        }\n      } catch (error: unknown) {\n        results.warnings.push(`Metadata edge promoter failed for ${fileResult.filePath}: ${toErrorMessage(error)}`);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n    return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n  }\n  ctx.onPhase?.('post-processing');\n\n  if (filesToDelete.length > 0) {\n    if (results.failed === 0) {\n      const staleDeleteResult = deleteStaleIndexedRecords(filesToDelete);\n      results.staleDeleted = staleDeleteResult.deleted;\n      results.staleDeleteFailed = staleDeleteResult.failed;\n      scanAppliedActions.push(...staleDeleteResult.actions);\n    } else {\n      console.warn('[memory-index-scan] Deferring stale cleanup because one or more replacement files failed to index');\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Time each un-yielded tail phase: because these phases do not yield, their\n  // wall-clock equals their event-loop-block duration, so this pinpoints a blocking\n  // phase when read alongside the event-loop lag sampler. Entering a phase also fires\n  // onPhase, which refreshes the busy marker — giving each phase a full TTL ahead.\n  const timedPhase = async <T>(phase: string, fn: () => Promise<T> | T): Promise<T> => {\n    ctx.onPhase?.(phase);\n    if (!instrument) {\n      return await fn();\n    }\n    const startedAt = Date.now();\n    try {\n      return await fn();\n    } finally {\n      console.error(`[memory-index-scan] phase=${phase} ms=${Date.now() - startedAt}`);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const orphanSweepResult = await timedPhase('orphan-sweep', () => runGlobalOrphanSweep());\n  results.orphanSwept = orphanSweepResult.swept;\n  results.orphanSweepFailed = orphanSweepResult.failed;\n  results.orphanSweepScanned = orphanSweepResult.scannedRows;\n  results.orphanSweepNextCursor = orphanSweepResult.nextCursor;\n  scanAppliedActions.push(...orphanSweepResult.actions);\n\n  results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired = await timedPhase('enrichment-repair', () => runPostInsertEnrichmentRepairBackfill());\n  if (results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired > 0) {\n    scanAppliedActions.push(createStatediffAction('upsert', {\n      target: 'graph_edge',\n      key: 'post-insert-enrichment-repair',\n      sourceOperation: 'scan',\n      metadata: { postInsertEnrichmentRepaired: results.postInsertEnrichmentRepaired },\n    }));\n  }\n\n  results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill = await timedPhase('trigger-backfill', () =>\n    runTriggerEmbeddingBackfill(requireDb(), { isCancelled: () => ctx.isCancelled?.() ?? false }));\n  if (triggerBackfillChangedRows(results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill)) {\n    scanAppliedActions.push(createTriggerBackfillAction(results.triggerEmbeddingBackfill));\n  }\n  await timedPhase('near-dup-repair', () => runNearDuplicateRepairBackfill());\n\n  // Create causal chains between spec folder documents.\n  // Includes deferred indexing outcomes and incremental single-file updates.\n  if (include_spec_docs) {\n    try {\n      // Determine which spec folders had spec document changes in this scan.\n      // We use parsed document type (not basename) to avoid false positives\n      // From memory/plan.md or similar filenames.\n      const affectedSpecFolders = new Set<string>();\n      for (const fileResult of results.files) {\n        if (!fileResult.specFolder || fileResult.status === 'failed') {\n          continue;\n        }\n\n        if (!fileResult.filePath) {\n          continue;\n        }\n\n        const docType = memoryParser.extractDocumentType(fileResult.filePath);\n        if (\n          docType !== 'memory' &&\n          docType !== 'constitutional'\n        ) {\n          affectedSpecFolders.add(fileResult.specFolder);\n        }\n      }\n\n      if (affectedSpecFolders.size > 0) {\n        const database = requireDb();\n        const { createSpecDocumentChain, init: initCausalEdges } = await import('../lib/storage/causal-edges.js');\n        initCausalEdges(database);\n\n        // Build full per-folder document map from DB (not just this scan's files).\n        const selectDocIds = database.prepare(`\n          SELECT document_type, MAX(id) AS id\n          FROM memory_index\n          WHERE spec_folder = ?\n            AND document_type IN ('spec', 'plan', 'tasks', 'checklist', 'decision_record', 'implementation_summary', 'research', 'handover', 'graph_metadata')\n          GROUP BY document_type\n        `);\n\n        let chainsCreated = 0;\n        let foldersProcessed = 0;\n        let chainYieldCount = 0;\n\n        for (const folder of affectedSpecFolders) {\n          // Per-folder synchronous DB work; yield + cancel-check between folders so a\n          // large affected set cannot block the event loop (same rationale as the\n          // metadata-edge sweep above).\n          if (++chainYieldCount % 50 === 0) {\n            if (ctx.isCancelled?.()) {\n              return cancelledScanEnvelope(scanKey);\n            }\n            await new Promise<void>((resolve) => setImmediate(resolve));\n          }\n          const rows = selectDocIds.all(folder) as Array<{ document_type: string; id: number }>;\n          const docIds: Record<string, number> = {};\n\n          for (const row of rows) {\n            if (row.document_type && typeof row.id === 'number') {","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1321,"totalLines":1322,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-index.ts","time":{"start":1781719870249,"end":1781719870256}},"id":"prt_ed6c7a76b001jAD9Fw6LdFfrhF","sessionID":"ses_1293965fbffeGe26eJeRcTpyq8","messageID":"msg_ed6c75a86001qw2iF87z3LK0Ab"}}
